'''Erling Braut Haaland''' ({{ne|'''Håland'''}};<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bekkestad |first=Oda Karlsen |date=6 December 2023 |title=Haalands millionhemmelighet: – Har tilgang på veldig avansert skatterådgivning |url=https://www.nettavisen.no/5-95-1498628 |access-date=12 October 2025 |website=Nettavisen |language=no}}</ref> {{IPA|no-NO-03|ˈhòːlɑn|lang}};<ref>{{cite Berulfsen 1969|page=144}}</ref> born 21 July 2000) is a <!--Do not add English or British born! Per MOS:BLPLEAD and MOS:CONTEXTBIO unless ethnicity contributes to notability, it should not be mentioned in opening. Please use the talk page to discuss notability before adding.-->Norwegian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Striker (association football)|striker]] for {{English football updater|ManchesC}} club [[Manchester City F.C.|Manchester City]] and the [[Norway national football team|Norway national team]]. Considered one of the best players in the world, and the greatest Norwegian player ever, he is known for his speed, strength, positioning, and finishing [[Penalty area|inside the box]].

Haaland began his senior career with [[Bryne FK|Bryne]] and [[Molde FK|Molde]] before signing with [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] in 2019, where he won the [[Austrian Bundesliga]] and [[Austrian Cup]]. He joined [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] in 2020, where he won the [[DFB-Pokal]] in [[2021 DFB-Pokal final|2021]]. In 2022, Haaland transferred to Manchester City for a fee of €60&nbsp;million (£51.2&nbsp;million) and won the [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]] in [[2022–23 Manchester City F.C. season|his debut campaign]]: he set the record for most goals scored by a player in a [[Premier League]] season (36) and most goals by a Premier League player in all competitions in one season (52),<ref>{{cite news |title=Haaland breaks Premier League goalscoring record |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-all-time-premier-league-goal-record-63818125 |access-date=3 May 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |archive-date=3 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230503210621/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-all-time-premier-league-goal-record-63818125 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=":7" /> winning the [[Premier League Golden Boot]], [[European Golden Shoe]] and the [[Gerd Müller Trophy]]. He was named [[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award|UEFA Men's Player of the Year]], [[IFFHS World's Best Player]], and finished runner-up in the [[2023 Ballon d'Or|Ballon d'Or]]. Haaland ranks as Manchester City's fourth-highest [[List of Manchester City F.C. records and statistics#Goalscorers|all-time top goalscorer]].

Haaland has won several individual awards and holds numerous records: he is the only player to win [[Premier League]] [[Premier League Young Player of the Season|Young Player]] and [[Premier League Player of the Season|Player of the Season]] in one season. He won the 2020 [[Golden Boy (award)|Golden Boy]], was named Bundesliga Player of the Season in 2021, and was included in the [[FIFA FIFPro World11]] for [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2021|2021]], [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2022|2022]], [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2023|2023]] and [[The Best FIFA Football Awards 2024|2024]]. He has scored the [[Premier League records and statistics#Goalscoring|most goals in a Premier League season]] and is the quickest player to [[List of Premier League hat-tricks|score eight hat-tricks]].

Haaland represented Norway at youth level, winning the [[FIFA U-20 World Cup#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] at the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]], where he scored a record nine goals in a single match. He made his senior international debut for Norway in 2019, and has since scored 55 goals in 48 appearances, making him Norway's [[Norway national football team#Top goalscorers|all-time top goalscorer]]. Haaland is the fastest player to reach [[List of men's footballers with 50 or more international goals|50 international goals]], doing so in just 46 games.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Orme |first=Daniel |date=2026-05-02 |title=Paul Merson tells Arsenal they have finally found their own Erling Haaland |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/paul-merson-haaland-arsenal-gyokeres-37103584 |access-date=2026-05-04 |website=Daily Mirror |language=en}}</ref>

== Early life ==
Erling Braut Haaland<ref>{{cite web |title=Derfor byttet han fra Håland til Haaland |trans-title=The reason he changed from Håland to Haaland |language=no |newspaper=Dagbladet |date=19 September 2019 |access-date=19 December 2019 |url=https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/derfor-byttet-han-fra-haland-til-haaland/71617171/amp |archive-date=3 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200203185824/https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/derfor-byttet-han-fra-haland-til-haaland/71617171/amp |url-status=live}}</ref> was born Erling Braut Håland<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/document/FWYC/2019/pdf/FWYC_2019_SquadLists.pdf |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup Poland 2019: List of Players: Norway |publisher=FIFA |page=13 |date=13 June 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200206013743/https://www.fifadata.com/document/FWYC/2019/pdf/FWYC_2019_SquadLists.pdf |archive-date=6 February 2020}}</ref> on 21 July 2000<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/253989/erling-haaland |title=Erling Haaland: Overview |work=ESPN |access-date=27 November 2020 |archive-date=27 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127150717/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/player/_/id/253989/erling-haaland |url-status=live}}</ref> in [[Leeds]], West Yorkshire<!-- DO NOT REMOVE "West Yorkshire", there are multiple "Leeds" in England, one cannot force a user to click the link to know which Leeds is meant here per "MOS:FORCELINK". Also, DO NOT LINK, see "MOS:GEOLINK" for further guidance -->, England, as his father [[Alfie Haaland]] was playing for [[Leeds United F.C.|Leeds United]] in the Premier League at the time.<ref name="Cross">{{cite news |url=https://www.leeds-live.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/erling-haaland-leeds-united-manutd-14854128 |title=Wonderkid Haaland would pick Leeds United over Man Utd every time |last=Cross |first=Beren |date=9 July 2018 |website=Leeds Live |access-date=22 November 2019 |archive-date=16 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416231306/https://www.leeds-live.co.uk/sport/leeds-united/erling-haaland-molde-leeds-united-14854128 |url-status=live}}</ref> As a result, Haaland stated that he grew up as a supporter of [[Leeds United]].<ref name="Cross"/> In 2004, at the age of three, he moved to [[Bryne]], his parents' hometown in Norway.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Hansen |first=Ole Jonny Eriksrud |date=29 November 2018 |title=Erling Braut Haaland: – Har sagt til meg selv at jeg vil bli verdens beste spiller |url=http://nettavisen.no/artikkel/3423560463|access-date=31 October 2020 |website=Nettavisen |language=no|archive-date=16 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416231307/https://www.nettavisen.no/artikkel/erling-braut-haaland-har-sagt-til-meg-selv-at-jeg-vil-bli-verdens-beste-spiller/s/12-95-3423560463|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Rose |first=Gary |date=2 October 2019 |title=Erling Braut Haaland: Is Red Bull Salzburg striker really 'the next Zlatan Ibrahimovic'? |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49885026 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=28 October 2019 |archive-date=2 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002060355/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/49885026 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Along with playing football from an early age, Haaland took part in various other sports as a child, including [[handball]], golf, and track and field.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/elring-haaland-interview-clicked-with-sancho-reus-and-hazard-straight-away-9952 |title=Erling Haaland: "I clicked with Jadon Sancho, Marco Reus and Thorgan Hazard straight away" |website=bundesliga.com |date=14 February 2020|access-date=20 February 2021|archive-date=20 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201120220559/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/elring-haaland-interview-clicked-with-sancho-reus-and-hazard-straight-away-9952|url-status=live}}</ref> He also reportedly achieved a world record in his age category for the [[standing long jump]] when he was five, with a recorded distance of 1.63 metres in 2006.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.90min.com/in/posts/6560333-stunning-report-reveals-erling-braut-haaland-is-a-world-record-holder-in-athletics |title=Stunning Report Reveals Erling Braut Haaland is a World Record Holder in Athletics |last=Arora |first=Mudeet |website=90min |date=19 February 2020|access-date=20 February 2021|archive-date=16 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416231303/https://www.90min.com/in/posts/6560333-stunning-report-reveals-erling-braut-haaland-is-a-world-record-holder-in-athletics|url-status=live}}</ref>

== Club career ==

=== Bryne ===
Haaland started in the academy of his hometown club [[Bryne FK|Bryne]] at the age of five.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Godø |first1=Øyvind |title=Slik ble Erling Braut Haaland en av heteste fotballspillere – Han kunne ikke løpe skikkelig |url=https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/han-kunne-ikke-lope-skikkelig/72073154 |newspaper=Dagbladet |access-date=2 September 2020 |date=30 January 2020 |archive-date=30 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200130134208/https://www.dagbladet.no/sport/han-kunne-ikke-lope-skikkelig/72073154 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="BL Background">{{cite web |title=Erling Haaland's journey: from Bryne to Borussia Dortmund |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/erling-haaland-roots-from-bryne-to-borussia-dortmund-history-norway-solskjaer-10652 |publisher=Bundesliga |access-date=2 September 2020 |archive-date=31 May 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200531212502/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/erling-haaland-roots-from-bryne-to-borussia-dortmund-history-norway-solskjaer-10652}}</ref>

During the [[2015 Norwegian Third Division|2015]] and [[2016 Norwegian Third Division|2016 seasons]], Haaland played for [[Bryne FK 2|Bryne 2]] (Bryne's reserve team) in the [[Norwegian Third Division|Norwegian fourth tier]] and impressed, scoring 18 goals in 18 matches. He debuted for Bryne 2 on 3 August 2015 in Group 6 of the 2015 Third Division in a 5–0 home win against [[Tollnes BK|Tollnes]]<ref name=nff>{{NFF|4166302}}</ref> and four days later he scored his first goal on senior level against [[Ålgård FK|Ålgård]] in a 3–2 defeat away.<ref>{{cite news|title=Hålands første seniormål|last=Sel|first=Tarjei|date=10 August 2015|work=Jærbladet|page=15|language=no}}</ref> The following season he appeared more often in the Bryne 2 squad and scored his first career hat-trick<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://90soccer.com/erling-haalands-beginnings-in-the-norwegian-fourth-division/ |title=Erling Haaland's beginnings in the Norwegian fourth division |website=90soccer.com |date=19 January 2024 }}</ref> on 19 September 2016, aged 16 and 2 months, in an away 5–3 win over [[SK Vard Haugesund 2|Vard Haugesund 2]] in the Group 6 of the Norwegian fourth tier.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fotball.no/fotballdata/kamp/?fiksId=6380531 |title=Kampreferat av Vard Haugesund 2 – Bryne 2 (3–5) – 19.09.2016 19.00 |publisher=fotball.no}}</ref>

In May 2016, Gaute Larsen was sacked as Bryne manager, and youth coach Berntsen was promoted to [[caretaker manager]]. Having worked closely with Haaland in other youth teams, the interim manager handed the teenager his first start, three months before his 16th birthday.<ref name="goal-background1">{{cite web |last1=König |first1=Nicklas |last2=Schmeckel |first2=Maximilian |title=Behind Haaland's Unstoppable Rise |url=https://www.goal.com/story/erling-haaland-unstoppable-rise/ |website=Goal (website) |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=2 September 2020 |archive-date=18 March 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200318114617/https://www.goal.com/story/erling-haaland-unstoppable-rise/}}</ref><ref name="BL Background" /> His first game with Bryne FK was a second-tier [[1. divisjon]] match against [[Ranheim Fotball|Ranheim]] on 12 May.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Rødt kort og tap da Håland debuterte |newspaper=Jærbladet |language=no |date=12 May 2016 |access-date=30 April 2018 |url=http://jbl.no/index.php?page=vis_nyhet&NyhetID=39447 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180625161118/http://jbl.no/index.php?page=vis_nyhet&NyhetID=39447 |archive-date=25 June 2018}}</ref>

After having initially being deployed as a [[Winger (association football)|winger]], Berntsen put Haaland in his favoured central role as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] after a few matches. Although he failed to score in his breakthrough season at Bryne, Haaland was offered a trial by German club [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|TSG Hoffenheim]] before eventually moving to [[Molde FK|Molde]] to play under [[Ole Gunnar Solskjær]].<ref name="goal-background1" /> Haaland made 16 total senior appearances for Bryne.<ref name=nff/>

=== Molde ===
[[File:Molde-Zenit (2) Erling Braut Håland 2018-8-30.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|Haaland playing for [[Molde FK|Molde]] in 2018]]

On 1 February 2017, Molde announced the signing of 16-year-old Haaland.<ref>{{Cite web |title=HÅLAND KLAR FOR MOLDE FK |publisher=Molde FK |language=no |date=1 February 2017 |access-date=30 April 2018 |url=http://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/haland-klar-for-molde-fk |archive-date=2 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180702175707/http://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/haland-klar-for-molde-fk |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 26 April in a [[Norwegian Football Cup|Norwegian Cup]] match against [[Volda TI]], scoring on his debut in a 3–2 win.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Solskjær hyller stortalentet Erling Braut Håland (17): – Ekkel å spille mot |trans-title=Solskjær praises huge talent Erling Braut Håland (17): – Hard to play against |language=no |newspaper=Verdens Gang |date=6 August 2018 |access-date=30 April 2018 |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/VVnp4/solskjaer-hyller-stortalentet-erling-braut-haaland-17-ekkel-aa-spille-mot |archive-date=30 April 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180430183007/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/VVnp4/solskjaer-hyller-stortalentet-erling-braut-haaland-17-ekkel-aa-spille-mot |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland's debut in the [[Eliteserien]] came on 4 June, being brought on as a 71st-minute [[Substitute (association football)|substitute]] against [[Sarpsborg 08 FF|Sarpsborg 08]] and receiving a yellow card in just over a minute of play on the pitch.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Alfies sønn (16) fikk Molde-debut: Gult kort etter 65 sekunder |trans-title=Alfie's son (16) got his Molde debut: Yellow card after 65 seconds |language=no |newspaper=Verdens Gang |date=5 June 2017 |access-date=30 April 2018 |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/vR084/alfies-soenn-16-fikk-molde-debut-gult-kort-etter-65-sekunder |archive-date=13 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200213220610/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/vR084/alfies-soenn-16-fikk-molde-debut-gult-kort-etter-65-sekunder |url-status=live}}</ref> On 6 August 2017, Haaland scored the winner for Molde in the 77th minute against [[Tromsø IL]], his first goal in the league.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Supertalentet (17) fikk Solskjær til å måpe: – Han er så tøff |trans-title=The super talent (17) made Solskjaer smirk: "He's so tough" |language=no |website=Nettavisen |date=6 August 2017 |access-date=28 June 2023 |url=https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/supertalentet-17-fikk-solskjar-til-a-mape-han-er-sa-toff/s/12-95-3423361579 |archive-date=10 July 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230710092250/https://www.nettavisen.no/sport/fotball/supertalentet-17-fikk-solskjar-til-a-mape-han-er-sa-toff/s/12-95-3423361579 |url-status=live}}</ref> His second strike of the season came on 17 September, as he bagged the decisive goal against [[Viking FK]] in a 3–2 victory. In the aftermath of the game, Haaland received criticism from teammate [[Björn Bergmann Sigurðarson]] for celebrating his goal towards Viking supporters.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/O4OAA/molde-helten-17-refses-av-lagkamerat-det-faar-han-ikke-gjoere-igjen |title=Molde-helten (17) refses av lagkamerat: – Det får han ikke gjøre igjen |first=Arilas Berg |last=Ould-Saada |date=18 September 2017 |newspaper=Verdens Gang |access-date=23 October 2019 |archive-date=12 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191012144046/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/O4OAA/molde-helten-17-refses-av-lagkamerat-det-faar-han-ikke-gjoere-igjen |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland finished his first season at Molde with four goals in 20 appearances.<ref>{{cite web |title=alyomfotball.no: Erling Braut Haaland – Tipico Bundesliga |url=http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=304980&tournamentId=247&useFullUrl=false |publisher=alt om fotball |access-date=2 September 2020 |archive-date=27 November 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201127194929/http://www.altomfotball.no/element.do?cmd=player&personId=304980&tournamentId=247&useFullUrl=false |url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 1 July 2018, Haaland scored four goals in the opening 21 minutes against [[SK Brann|Brann]], securing his team a 4–0 victory over the unbeaten league leaders at the time. After the match, Molde manager Ole Gunnar Solskjær compared Haaland's style of play to Belgian forward [[Romelu Lukaku]], and said the club had rejected several bids for the striker from different clubs.<ref>{{Cite news |title=Manchester United scout watches wonderkid Erling Haaland score FOUR goals |trans-title=Manchester United scout watches wonderkid Erling Haaland score FOUR goals |newspaper=Manchester Evening News |date=2 July 2018 |access-date=7 July 2018 |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-utd-transfer-erling-haland-14853170 |archive-date=7 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180707172425/https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/transfer-news/man-utd-transfer-erling-haland-14853170 |url-status=live}}</ref> In the following match a week later, Haaland continued his scoring run with a brace against [[Vålerenga Fotball|Vålerenga]] in a 5–1 win.<ref>{{Cite web |title=LEKESTUE! |trans-title=LEKESTUE! |publisher=Molde FK |date=8 July 2018 |access-date=8 July 2018 |url=http://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/lekestue-mot-vif |archive-date=9 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180709011228/http://www.moldefk.no/nyheter/lekestue-mot-vif |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his first goal in [[UEFA]] competition on 26 July, converting a penalty in Molde's 3–0 [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League qualifying phase and play-off round|Europa League qualifying]] victory against [[KF Laçi]].<ref>{{Cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/uefa-europa-league/2018-2019/haland-scoring-da-molde-dominerte-mot-albanske_leci_mfk_sto6863926/story.shtml |title=Håland-scoring da Molde dominerte mot albanske Laci |publisher=Eurosport |date=26 July 2018 |access-date=26 July 2018 |archive-date=26 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180726234457/https://www.eurosport.no/fotball/uefa-europa-league/2018-2019/haland-scoring-da-molde-dominerte-mot-albanske_leci_mfk_sto6863926/story.shtml |url-status=live}}</ref> Due to a sprained ankle, Haaland did not participate in Molde's last three league matches of the season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/0Ed8WM/skadet-haaland-trolig-ferdigspilt-i-molde |title=Skadet Håland trolig ferdigspilt i Molde |first=Arilas Berg |last=Ould-Saada |language=no |date=1 November 2018 |newspaper=Verdens Gang |access-date=23 October 2019 |archive-date=5 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205153403/https://www.vg.no/sport/fotball/i/0Ed8WM/skadet-haaland-trolig-ferdigspilt-i-molde |url-status=live}}</ref> For his performances in the [[2018 Eliteserien]], Haaland received the [[Kniksen Award#Breakthrough of the Year|Eliteserien Breakthrough of the Year award]].<ref name="breakthrough award">{{cite web |url=https://www.eliteserien.no/fotballfesten/alle-vinnerne-pa-fotballfesten |title=Alle vinnerne på fotballfesten |language=no |publisher=Eliteserien |date=25 November 2018 |access-date=20 March 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181127152124/https://www.eliteserien.no/fotballfesten/alle-vinnerne-pa-fotballfesten |archive-date=27 November 2018 |url-status=dead}}</ref> He finished the [[2018 Molde FK season|2018 season]] as Molde's top goalscorer, scoring 16 goals in 30 matches across all competitions.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Erling Braut Haaland: – Har sagt til meg selv at jeg vil bli verdens beste spiller |trans-title=Erling Braut Haaland: – Told myself I want to become the world's best player |publisher=Nettavisen |language=no |date=28 November 2019 |access-date=2 March 2020 |url=https://www.nettavisen.no/nyheter/erling-braut-haaland---har-sagt-til-meg-selv-at-jeg-vil-bli-verdens-beste-spiller/3423560463.html |archive-date=14 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191214155943/https://www.nettavisen.no/nyheter/erling-braut-haaland---har-sagt-til-meg-selv-at-jeg-vil-bli-verdens-beste-spiller/3423560463.html}}</ref>

=== Red Bull Salzburg ===
[[File:FC RB Salzburg versus SV Mattersburg (4. Juli 2019) 29.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|Haaland playing for Red Bull Salzburg in 2019]]

On 19 August 2018, [[Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian Bundesliga]] champions Red Bull Salzburg announced that Haaland would join the club on 1 January 2019, signing a five-year contract.<ref name=":0">{{cite web |title=Servus in Salzburg, Erling Haland! |url=https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/fc-red-bull-salzburg/news/saison_2018_19/servus-in-salzburg-erling-haland.html |publisher=FC Red Bull Salzburg |access-date=19 August 2018 |language=de |date=19 August 2018 |archive-date=18 August 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180818214857/https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/de/fc-red-bull-salzburg/news/saison_2018_19/servus-in-salzburg-erling-haland.html}}</ref> ''[[The Athletic]]''{{'}}s Phil Hay would later reveal that prior to his move to Salzburg, Haaland was also subject of an offer from his father's former club Leeds United.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://sportslens.com/phil-hay-says-leeds-united-attempted-to-sign-erling-haaland-last-year/276192/ |title=Phil Hay says Leeds United attempted to sign Erling Haaland last year |website=Sportslens.com |date=18 September 2019 |access-date=4 January 2020 |archive-date=21 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221001731/https://sportslens.com/phil-hay-says-leeds-united-attempted-to-sign-erling-haaland-last-year/276192/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 17 February, the [[2018–19 Austrian Cup]] quarter-finals against [[1. Wiener Neustädter SC (2008)|Wiener Neustädter]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/02/17/austria/ofb-stiegl-cup/wiener-neustadt/salzburg/2931711/|title=Wiener Neustadt vs. Salzburg 0–6: Summary|website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> and scored his first goal on 12 May in the Austrian Bundesliga 2–1 win over [[LASK]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/matches/2019/05/12/austria/bundesliga/salzburg/lask/2999831/|title=Salzburg vs. LASK 2–1: Summary|website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref>

On 19 July, he scored his first [[Hat-trick (association football)|hat-trick]] for the club in a 7–1 [[Austrian Cup]] win against [[SC-ESV Parndorf 1919|SC-ESV Parndorf]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/19/austria/ofb-stiegl-cup/sc-esv-parndorf-1919/fc-red-bull-salzburg/3048847/ |title=Parndorf vs. Salzburg 1–7: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=1 September 2021 |archive-date=11 September 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190911024856/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/07/19/austria/ofb-stiegl-cup/sc-esv-parndorf-1919/fc-red-bull-salzburg/3048847/ |url-status=live}}</ref> and followed this up with his first hat-trick in the league on 10 August, scoring three in a 5–2 victory against [[Wolfsberger AC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/10/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/wolfsberger-athletik-club/3034849/ |title=Salzburg vs. Wolfsberger AC 5–2: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=1 September 2021 |archive-date=27 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190827204919/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/08/10/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/wolfsberger-athletik-club/3034849/ |url-status=live}}</ref> He got a third hat-trick for Salzburg on 14 September in a 7–2 victory over [[TSV Hartberg]]; this was the sixth consecutive league game Haaland had scored in, with 11 total goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/14/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/tsv-hartberg/3034873/ |title=Salzburg vs. Hartberg 7–2: Summary |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |access-date=1 September 2021 |archive-date=18 August 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190818041432/https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2019/09/14/austria/bundesliga/fc-red-bull-salzburg/tsv-hartberg/3034873/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Three days later, Haaland made his debut in the [[UEFA Champions League]] against [[K.R.C. Genk|Genk]], where he scored three goals in the first half of an eventual 6–2 victory, his fourth overall hat-trick for Salzburg,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/sep/17/champions-league-roundup-haland-makes-history-in-salzburg-romp-as-barca-are-held |title=Champions League roundup: Håland makes history in Salzburg romp as Barça are held |newspaper=The Guardian |date=17 September 2019 |access-date=17 September 2019 |archive-date=2 October 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191002172228/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2019/sep/17/champions-league-roundup-haland-makes-history-in-salzburg-romp-as-barca-are-held |url-status=live}}</ref> becoming the only player to score a first-half hat-trick on competition debut.<ref name=":6" />

In his next two matches of the Champions League season, Haaland recorded a goal against [[Liverpool F.C.|Liverpool]] at [[Anfield]] and a further two against [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]], becoming only the second teenager after [[Karim Benzema]] in the history of the competition to score in each of his first three appearances. His six goals were also the most scored by any player in their first three Champions League matches.<ref name="goal">{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/salzburgs-haaland-matches-drogbas-champions-league-record/rij8a810gbsn1bai6ycxrok8x |title=Salzburg's Haaland matches Drogba's Champions League record |website=Goal (website) |publisher=Perform Group |date=24 October 2019 |access-date=5 November 2019 |archive-date=2 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202021948/https://www.goal.com/en-cm/news/salzburgs-haaland-matches-drogbas-champions-league-record/rij8a810gbsn1bai6ycxrok8x |url-status=live}}</ref> After converting a penalty in Salzburg's reverse fixture against Napoli, Haaland became the first teenager to score in his first four matches in the competition, and only the fourth player of any age to achieve this feat, following [[Zé Carlos (footballer, born 1965)|Zé Carlos]], [[Alessandro Del Piero]] and [[Diego Costa]].<ref name=":1">{{cite web |url=https://www.sport1.de/fussball/champions-league/2019/11/champions-league-erling-haaland-von-red-bull-trifft-auch-gegen-neapel |title=Haaland ballert sich zum Rekord |publisher=Sport1 |language=de |date=5 November 2019 |access-date=5 November 2019 |archive-date=6 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191106121924/https://www.sport1.de/fussball/champions-league/2019/11/champions-league-erling-haaland-von-red-bull-trifft-auch-gegen-neapel |url-status=live}}</ref> He then scored all three goals in Salzburg's 3–0 victory at Wolfsberger AC on 10 November, recording his fifth hat-trick of the season and his second against the club.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/11/10/football/1573410028_663896.html |title=Erling Braut Haaland bags fifth hat-trick of the season |newspaper=Diario AS |location=Madrid |date=10 November 2019 |access-date=19 December 2019 |archive-date=9 June 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200609094257/https://en.as.com/en/2019/11/10/football/1573410028_663896.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 27 November, Haaland came off the bench to score another goal against Genk, joining Del Piero, [[Serhiy Rebrov]], [[Neymar]], [[Cristiano Ronaldo]] and [[Robert Lewandowski]] as the only players to score in the first five matches of a Champions League group stage, and becoming the first teenager to score in five consecutive matches in the competition.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://en.as.com/en/2019/11/27/football/1574893540_950310.html |title=Erling Haaland makes Champions League history |newspaper=Diario AS |location=Madrid |date=27 November 2019 |access-date=19 December 2019 |archive-date=12 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200212123718/https://en.as.com/en/2019/11/27/football/1574893540_950310.html |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Genk 1–4 Red Bull Salzburg: Erling Braut Haaland breaks more scoring records |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519954 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=19 December 2019 |date=27 November 2019 |archive-date=28 November 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191128101920/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50519954 |url-status=live}}</ref> However, he would fail to find the net in Salzburg's final group match against Liverpool, as his team lost 2–0 and were eliminated from the competition.<ref>{{cite news |title=Red Bull Salzburg 0–2 Liverpool: Reds reach Champions League knockout stages with win |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50667332 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=19 December 2019 |date=10 December 2019 |archive-date=12 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191212170327/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50667332 |url-status=live}}</ref> This would prove to be Haaland's final game for the club; he departed Salzburg having recorded 29 goals, with 28 of these coming in only 22 appearances made during the [[2019–20 FC Red Bull Salzburg season|2019–20 season]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/11897354/erling-haaland-signs-for-borussia-dortmund-from-rb-salzburg |title=Dortmund sign Man Utd target Haaland |website=Sky Sports |date=30 December 2019 |access-date=30 December 2019 |archive-date=29 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191229214316/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/11897354/erling-haaland-signs-for-borussia-dortmund-from-rb-salzburg |url-status=live}}</ref>

=== Borussia Dortmund ===
==== 2019–20: Debut season ====
Despite being a reported target of [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]] and [[Juventus FC|Juventus]], [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] confirmed the signing of Haaland on 29 December 2019, three days before the winter transfer window opened, for a fee reported to be in the region of €20&nbsp;million, signing a four-and-a-half-year contract.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/BVB-verpflichtet-Erling-Haaland |title=BVB verplichtet Erling Haaland |language=de |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |date=29 December 2019 |access-date=29 December 2019 |archive-date=5 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200205184007/https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/BVB-verpflichtet-Erling-Haaland |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Erling Braut Haaland: Borussia Dortmund sign striker from Red Bull Salzburg |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50940894 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=31 December 2019 |date=29 December 2019 |archive-date=30 December 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191230183508/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/50940894 |url-status=live}}</ref>

Haaland made his debut for Dortmund away to [[FC Augsburg]] on 18 January 2020, coming on as a second-half substitute and scoring [[List of Bundesliga hat-tricks|a hat-trick]] within 23 minutes in a 5–3 win.<ref>{{cite news |title=FC Augsburg 3–5 Borussia Dortmund: Erling Braut Haaland scores hat-trick on debut |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51163405 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=18 January 2020 |date=18 January 2020 |archive-date=19 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200119112551/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51163405 |url-status=live}}</ref> This made him only the second player in Dortmund history after [[Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang]] to score three goals on their Bundesliga debut.<ref>{{cite web |last=Grez |first=Matias |date=18 January 2020 |title=Teen sensation Erling Braut Håland scores debut hat-trick to save Borussia Dortmund |url=https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/18/football/borussia-dortmund-erling-braut-hland-augsburg-spt-intl |access-date=20 January 2020 |work=CNN|archive-date=18 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200118232154/https://www.cnn.com/2020/01/18/football/borussia-dortmund-erling-braut-hland-augsburg-spt-intl/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Six days later, Haaland once again came off the bench, making his second club appearance in Dortmund's match against [[1. FC Köln|FC Köln]]. He scored after 12 minutes and netted a second goal 10 minutes later, contributing to a 5–1 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.kicker.de/dortmund-gegen-koeln-2020-bundesliga-4588821/ticker |title=Haaland glänzt auch beim Heimdebüt: BVB schießt Köln ab |website=kicker |publisher=Olympia-Verlag |language=de |access-date=25 January 2020 |archive-date=25 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125134630/https://www.kicker.de/4588821/ticker/borussia-dortmund-17/1-fc-koeln-16 |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland became the first Bundesliga player to score five goals in his opening two matches, as well as the fastest player to reach that tally (56 minutes played).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.bvb.de/eng/content/view/full/173172/ |title=Haaland's Bundesliga record – five goals in 56 minutes |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |access-date=25 January 2020 |archive-date=25 January 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200125031443/https://www.bvb.de/eng/content/view/full/173172 |url-status=live}}</ref> Despite being on the pitch in the league for only an hour, he won January's [[2019–20 Bundesliga#Monthly awards|Bundesliga Player of the Month]] award.<ref>{{cite news |title=Haaland wins Player of the Month award after an hour on pitch |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4053203/haaland-wins-player-of-the-month-award-after-an-hour-on-pitch |work=ESPN |access-date=18 February 2020 |date=15 February 2020 |archive-date=17 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200217002023/https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4053203/haaland-wins-player-of-the-month-award-after-an-hour-on-pitch |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland got a brace against [[1. FC Union Berlin|Union Berlin]] on 1 February, becoming the first player in history to score seven goals in their first three Bundesliga matches.<ref>{{cite web |title=Borussia Dortmund 5–0 Union Berlin: Jadon Sancho and Erling Braut Haaland break records |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51342031 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=1 February 2020 |date=3 February 2020 |archive-date=2 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200202212856/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51342031 |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 18 February, Haaland scored both Dortmund goals in their 2–1 first leg victory over [[Paris Saint-Germain F.C.|Paris Saint-Germain]] in the [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|Champions League round of 16]]. This brought his total to 10 Champions League goals for the 2019–20 campaign in only his eighth overall appearance in the competition, adding to the eight he had scored for Salzburg in the group stage.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Dawkes |first1=Phil |title=Borussia Dortmund 2–1 Paris St-Germain: Erling Braut Haaland scores twice |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51533266 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=19 February 2020 |date=18 February 2020 |archive-date=21 February 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200221011052/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51533266 |url-status=live}}</ref> Dortmund would lose 2–0 in the return leg on 11 March, however, as Haaland saw elimination from the competition for a second time in the same season.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Chowdhury |first1=Saj |title=Paris St-Germain 2–0 Borussia Dortmund: Neymar scores as French champions reach last eight |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51800667 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=11 March 2020 |date=11 March 2020 |archive-date=12 July 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200712095759/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51800667 |url-status=live}}</ref> Following the Bundesliga's return on 16 May in the midst of the ongoing [[COVID-19 pandemic in Germany|COVID-19 pandemic]], Haaland scored Dortmund's opener of their 4–0 [[Revierderby]] win over [[FC Schalke 04|Schalke 04]], his tenth goal of the Bundesliga season.<ref>{{cite web |title=Dortmund's Haaland scores Bundesliga's first goal upon league's return |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/german-bundesliga/story/4095187/dortmunds-erling-haaland-scores-bundesligas-first-goal-upon-leagues-return |date=16 May 2020 |work=ESPN|access-date=18 May 2020|archive-date=11 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200611060310/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/german-bundesliga/story/4095187/dortmunds-erling-haaland-scores-bundesligas-first-goal-upon-leagues-return|url-status=live}}</ref> On 20 June, he scored both goals in a 2–0 win against [[RB Leipzig]] to secure second place for Dortmund, which would lead to Champions League football in the following season.<ref>{{Cite web |date=20 June 2020 |title=Haaland goals secure Bundesliga runner-up spot for Dortmund |url=https://apnews.com/b25c961f959d34b4600bba4db0d567f7|access-date=26 June 2020 |website=Associated Press News|archive-date=29 June 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200629211450/https://apnews.com/b25c961f959d34b4600bba4db0d567f7|url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland concluded his 2019–20 campaign with 44 goals in 40 club appearances across all competitions played for both Salzburg and Dortmund.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/erling-haaland-talking-about-titles-alone-not-enough-borussia-dortmund-12226 |title=Borussia Dortmund's Erling Haaland: "Talking about winning titles alone is not enough" |website=bundesliga.com |date=29 July 2020|access-date=4 August 2020|archive-date=3 August 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200803233523/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/erling-haaland-talking-about-titles-alone-not-enough-borussia-dortmund-12226|url-status=live}}</ref>

==== 2020–21: UCL top scorer and DFB-Pokal title ====
[[File:Erling Haaland 2020.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|Haaland playing for Borussia Dortmund in 2020]]

On 19 September 2020, in Dortmund's first match of the new season, Haaland scored a brace in a 3–0 win over [[Borussia Mönchengladbach]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-bvb-doppelpacker-erling-haaland-zentrum-junge-wilde-12915 |title=Jung, entschlossen, talentiert – Borussia Dortmund begeistert zum Start |publisher=Bundesliga |language=de |date=September 2020 |access-date=22 November 2020 |archive-date=21 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201021132831/https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-bvb-doppelpacker-erling-haaland-zentrum-junge-wilde-12915 |url-status=live}}</ref> He scored his team's equaliser in their 2–3 [[Der Klassiker]] defeat to [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] in the [[2020 DFL-Supercup|DFL-Supercup]] on 30 September,<ref>{{cite web |date=30 September 2020 |title=Bayern Munich beat Borussia Dortmund to claim German Super Cup |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=577252 |work=ESPN |access-date=7 November 2020|archive-date=2 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201102094844/https://www.espn.com/soccer/report?gameId=577252|url-status=live}}</ref> and again found the net against Bayern when the sides met in the league on 7 November, with Dortmund losing 2–3 once more.<ref>{{cite web |date=7 November 2020 |title=Bayern hold on to win Klassiker thriller |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11881/12126576/borussia-dortmund-2-3-bayern-munich-bayern-top-bundesliga-as-robert-lewandowski-keeps-up-klassiker-form |website=Sky Sports|access-date=7 November 2020|archive-date=16 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416231304/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11881/12126576/borussia-dortmund-2-3-bayern-munich-bayern-top-bundesliga-as-robert-lewandowski-keeps-up-klassiker-form|url-status=live}}</ref> On 21 November, Haaland scored four goals in 32 minutes of a 5–2 away victory against [[Hertha BSC]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/content/view/full/183562 |title=Haaland scores four as BVB come from behind to win in Berlin |publisher=Borussia Dortmund |date=21 November 2020 |access-date=22 November 2020 |archive-date=4 December 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201204090915/https://www.bvb.de/eng/content/view/full/183562 |url-status=live}}</ref> These five goals in November saw him crowned the [[2020–21 Bundesliga#Monthly awards|Bundesliga Player of the Month]] for a second time.<ref name="November POTM" />

Haaland continued his goalscoring feats in the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]], scoring six times in the first four matches of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League group stage|2020–21 group stage]], with his brace in a 3–0 win over [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] on 24 November making him the fastest player to record 15 Champions League goals; he had reached this benchmark in 12 matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54868208 |title=Erling Braut Haaland: Will Borussia Dortmund striker fill Lionel Messi & Cristiano Ronaldo's shoes? |publisher=BBC Sport |date=24 November 2020 |access-date=24 November 2020 |archive-date=19 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219085323/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54868208 |url-status=live}}</ref> Hours before Dortmund's fifth group match against [[S.S. Lazio|Lazio]] on 2 December, however, the club announced that Haaland had suffered a hamstring injury, which kept him out of action until after the new year.<ref>{{cite news |date=2 December 2020 |title=Borussia Dortmund's Haaland to miss rest of 2020 through injury |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4251567/borussia-dortmunds-haaland-to-miss-rest-of-2020-through-injury |work=ESPN |access-date=3 December 2020|archive-date=2 December 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202210410/https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4251567/borussia-dortmunds-haaland-to-miss-rest-of-2020-through-injury|url-status=live}}</ref>

Haaland made his return against [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on 3 January 2021.<ref>{{cite web |date=1 January 2021 |title=Haaland back in action as Bundesliga returns from mini-break |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/haaland-back-in-action-as-bundesliga-returns-from-mini-break-934945 |website=BeSoccer |access-date=17 February 2021|archive-date=16 April 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210416231305/https://www.besoccer.com/new/amp/haaland-back-in-action-as-bundesliga-returns-from-mini-break-934945|url-status=live}}</ref> He scored a brace away against RB Leipzig in a 3–1 win on 9 January,<ref>{{cite news |date=9 January 2021 |title=Erling Haaland hits brace as Borussia Dortmund overcome RB Leipzig |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/rb-leipzig-borussia-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-sancho-szoboszlai-14194 |website=bundesliga.com |access-date=17 February 2021|archive-date=28 January 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210128093215/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/rb-leipzig-borussia-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-sancho-szoboszlai-14194|url-status=live}}</ref> and another two in a 4–2 defeat to Mönchengladbach on 22 January.<ref>{{cite news |date=22 January 2021 |title=Borussia Mönchengladbach leapfrog Borussia Dortmund in six-goal thriller |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-monchengladbach-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-sancho-14402 |website=bundesliga.com |access-date=17 February 2021|archive-date=15 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210215155533/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-monchengladbach-dortmund-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-sancho-14402|url-status=live}}</ref> On 17 February, he scored two goals in Dortmund's 3–2 away victory against [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the first leg of the [[2020–21 UEFA Champions League knockout phase#Round of 16|Champions League round of 16]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56039612 |title=Sevilla 2–3 Borussia Dortmund: Erling Braut Haaland puts Dortmund in charge of Champions League tie |publisher=BBC Sport |date=17 February 2021 |access-date=17 February 2021 |archive-date=17 February 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210217175519/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56039612 |url-status=live}}</ref> In Dortmund's reverse league fixture against Bayern at the [[Allianz Arena]] on 6 March, Haaland scored twice within the opening 10 minutes to give his team a 2–0 lead. However, he was substituted off in the second half after picking up a knock, as Bayern rallied to win the match 4–2.<ref>{{cite web |date=6 March 2021 |title=Robert Lewandowski reminds Erling Haaland of the Bundesliga pecking order |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/german-bundesliga/story/4330933/robert-lewandowski-reminds-erling-haaland-of-the-bundesliga-pecking-order |work=ESPN |access-date=7 March 2021|archive-date=7 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307014840/https://www.espn.com/soccer/german-bundesliga/story/4330933/robert-lewandowski-reminds-erling-haaland-of-the-bundesliga-pecking-order|url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland's second goal was the 100th of his senior career, reaching this milestone in 146 appearances.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.givemesport.com/1657177-haaland-messi-or-ronaldo-who-scored-100-goals-quickest-in-their-career |last=Hoskin |first=Rob |title=Haaland, Messi or Ronaldo: Who scored 100 goals quickest in their career? |website=GiveMeSport |date=7 March 2021 |access-date=7 March 2021|archive-date=8 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210308025006/https://www.givemesport.com/1657177-haaland-messi-or-ronaldo-who-scored-100-goals-quickest-in-their-career|url-status=live}}</ref>

Haaland scored another brace against Sevilla in the second leg on 9 March in a 2–2 draw, advancing to the quarter-finals 5–4 on aggregate.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56325186 |title=Borussia Dortmund 2–2 Sevilla |publisher=BBC Sport |date=9 March 2021 |access-date=9 March 2021 |archive-date=9 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309231532/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/56325186 |url-status=live}}</ref> With only 14 matches played, this made him both the fastest and youngest player to reach 20 goals in the competition, also becoming the first player to score multiple times in four consecutive Champions League appearances.<ref>{{cite news |date=9 March 2021 |title=Erling Haaland fastest and youngest to reach 20 Champions League goals |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0267-11c2243c2cc4-ef4d87bba67c-1000--haaland-fastest-to-20-goals/ |publisher=UEFA |access-date=9 March 2021|archive-date=9 March 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210309215610/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0267-11c2243c2cc4-ef4d87bba67c-1000--haaland-fastest-to-20-goals/|url-status=live}}</ref> After missing two matches due to deep bruising,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/dortmund-wait-on-injured-haaland-for-dfb-pokal-final-989727 |title=Dortmund wait on injured Haaland for DFB Pokal final |website=BeSoccer |date=8 May 2021|access-date=14 May 2021|archive-date=15 May 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210515050605/https://www.besoccer.com/new/dortmund-wait-on-injured-haaland-for-dfb-pokal-final-989727|url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland returned to Dortmund's starting line-up on 13 May for the [[2021 DFB-Pokal final]]; he scored a brace in his team's 4–1 win over Leipzig, securing his first title with the club.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2320839 |title=RB Leipzig 1–4 Borussia Dortmund |website=dfb.de |language=de |date=13 May 2021 |access-date=13 May 2021 |archive-date=8 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210508143314/https://www.dfb.de/dfb-pokal/spieltag/?spieledb_path=%2Fmatches%2F2320839 |url-status=live}}</ref> He ended the season with 41 goals in all competitions, including 27 in the league, which won him the fan-voted Bundesliga Player of the Season award,<ref name="goal21">{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/de/meldungen/haaland-spieler-der-saison-bundesliga-bvb-lewandowski/natrorjs169915wzfzoovcthb |title=BVB: Erling Haaland zum Spieler der Saison in der Bundesliga gekürt |website=Goal (website) |language=de |date=25 May 2021 |access-date=25 May 2021 |archive-date=26 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210526070855/https://www.goal.com/de/meldungen/haaland-spieler-der-saison-bundesliga-bvb-lewandowski/natrorjs169915wzfzoovcthb |url-status=live}}</ref> and finished the season as the top scorer of the Champions League with 10 goals,<ref name="scorer">{{cite news |url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Teams-goals188 |title=Champions League top scorer: Haaland finishes out in front |publisher=UEFA |date=29 May 2021 |access-date=29 May 2021 |archive-date=7 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210807220755/https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Teams-goals188 |url-status=live}}</ref> later being awarded the competition's [[UEFA Club Football Awards#Best Forward|best forward]].<ref name="UCL forward" />

==== 2021–22: Injury struggles and departure ====
Haaland started off the [[2021–22 Borussia Dortmund season|2021–22 season]] with a hat-trick versus [[SV Wehen Wiesbaden|Wehen Wiesbaden]] in the first round of the [[2021–22 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] on 7 August 2021.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/dfb-pokal-erling-haaland-erzielt-fuer-borussia-dortmund-in-der-ersten-runde-drei-tore-a-e1d17cd8-c1c7-4ab0-9a45-e4cad8842272 |title=Haaland startet mit drei Toren in die Saison |trans-title=Haaland starts the season with three goals |website=Spiegel Sport |date=7 August 2021 |access-date=7 August 2021 |language=de |archive-date=14 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210814213713/https://www.spiegel.de/sport/fussball/dfb-pokal-erling-haaland-erzielt-fuer-borussia-dortmund-in-der-ersten-runde-drei-tore-a-e1d17cd8-c1c7-4ab0-9a45-e4cad8842272 |url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, on matchday one of the [[2021–22 Bundesliga|Bundesliga]], he scored a brace and assisted two goals as Dortmund beat [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] 5–2.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-eintracht-frankfurt-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-16863 |title=Erling Haaland orchestrates big Borussia Dortmund win against Eintracht Frankfurt |publisher=Bundesliga |date=14 August 2021 |access-date=14 August 2021 |archive-date=11 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210911232155/https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/borussia-dortmund-eintracht-frankfurt-live-line-ups-stats-haaland-reyna-16863 |url-status=live}}</ref> During the first months of the season, Haaland was sidelined with a hamstring injury, returning on 16 October and scoring a brace against [[1. FSV Mainz 05|Mainz]] in a 3–1 victory.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lance.com.br/futebol-internacional/haaland-volta-apos-lesao-marca-duas-vezes-borussia-dortmund-vence-mainz-alemao.html |title=Haaland volta após lesão, marca duas vezes, e Borussia Dortmund vence o Mainz no Alemão |publisher=Lance |date=16 October 2021 |access-date=16 October 2021 |archive-date=16 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211016171826/https://www.lance.com.br/futebol-internacional/haaland-volta-apos-lesao-marca-duas-vezes-borussia-dortmund-vence-mainz-alemao.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Shortly after, Haaland suffered a hip flexor injury, which sidelined him for two months.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/12441202/erling-haaland-marco-rose-says-borussia-dortmund-forward-will-miss-a-few-weeks-with-hip-flexor-injury |title=Erling Haaland: Marco Rose says Borussia Dortmund forward will miss 'a few weeks' with hip flexor injury |website=Sky Sports |date=22 October 2021 |access-date=3 October 2021 |archive-date=24 October 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211024074754/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/12441202/erling-haaland-marco-rose-says-borussia-dortmund-forward-will-miss-a-few-weeks-with-hip-flexor-injury |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his return on 27 November, scoring his 50th Bundesliga goal in a 3–1 victory over Wolfsburg, setting a new record for the fewest appearances and also became the youngest player to score 50 league goals.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/borussia-dortmund/internacional/haaland-chega-aos-50-golos-na-bundesliga-e-faz-historia |title=Haaland chega aos 50 golos na Bundesliga e faz história |website=Maisfutebol |date=27 November 2021 |access-date=27 November 2021 |archive-date=27 November 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211127200527/https://maisfutebol.iol.pt/borussia-dortmund/internacional/haaland-chega-aos-50-golos-na-bundesliga-e-faz-historia |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 10 May, Dortmund announced that Haaland would be leaving at the end of the season to sign for Premier League club Manchester City.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/transfers/2021-2022/erling-haalands-manchester-city-transfer-confirmed-with-forward-to-leave-borussia-dortmund_sto8918824/story.shtml |title=ERLING HAALAND'S MANCHESTER CITY TRANSFER CONFIRMED WITH FORWARD TO LEAVE BORUSSIA DORTMUND, REPLACED BY KARIM ADEYEMI |publisher=Eurosport |date=11 May 2022 |access-date=26 May 2020 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111832/https://www.eurosport.com/geoblocking.shtml |url-status=live}}</ref> Four days later, he bid farewell to the club at the [[Westfalenstadion]] prior to Dortmund's final match against Hertha BSC, and scored Dortmund's first goal in a 2–1 win.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.aa.com.tr/en/sports/haaland-bids-farewell-to-borussia-dortmund-scores-against-hertha-berlin/2588156 |publisher=Anadolu Agency |date=14 May 2022|access-date=26 May 2020 |title=Haaland bids farewell to Borussia Dortmund, scores against Hertha Berlin|archive-date=16 May 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220516092541/https://www.aa.com.tr/en/sports/haaland-bids-farewell-to-borussia-dortmund-scores-against-hertha-berlin/2588156|url-status=live}}</ref>

===Manchester City===
====2022–23: Record-breaking debut season and continental treble====
[[File:WolvesvManCitySeptember2022 2 (cropped).jpg|thumb|Haaland (centre) playing for Manchester City against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]] in 2022]]

On 10 May 2022, Premier League club Manchester City announced they had reached a deal to sign Haaland after activating his €60&nbsp;million (£51.2&nbsp;million) [[Buyout clause|release clause]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Erling Haaland: Manchester City agree to sign Norway striker from Borussia Dortmund for £51.2m |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/60819647 |date=10 May 2022 |access-date=10 May 2022 |publisher=BBC Sport |archive-date=10 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220510144836/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/60819647 |url-status=live}}</ref> The deal was formalised on 13 June, with City confirming that Haaland would be joining the club on 1 July on a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite news |date=13 June 2022 |access-date=13 June 2022 |title=City complete Haaland transfer |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-manchester-city-transfer-complete-63790702 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |archive-date=13 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220613215152/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-manchester-city-transfer-complete-63790702 |url-status=live}}</ref> He made his competitive debut on 30 July, playing 90 minutes of a 3–1 defeat to Liverpool in the [[2022 FA Community Shield]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Bosher |first=Luke |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/3463035/2022/07/30/pep-guardiola-erling-haaland-manchester-city/ |title=Guardiola after Man City's Community Shield defeat: 'It is good for Haaland to see the reality in a new country' |date=30 July 2022 |access-date=2 October 2022 |website=The Athletic |archive-date=2 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221002154721/https://theathletic.com/3463035/2022/07/30/pep-guardiola-erling-haaland-manchester-city/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Haaland scored twice on his [[2022–23 Premier League|league]] debut against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] on 7 August 2022, the only goals of a 2–0 away victory.<ref>{{cite news |date=7 August 2022 |title=Erling Haaland 'born to score goals', says Pep Guardiola after City victory |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/07/erling-haaland-born-to-score-goals-says-pep-guardiola-after-city-victory |access-date=8 August 2022 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |archive-date=25 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220925100647/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/07/erling-haaland-born-to-score-goals-says-pep-guardiola-after-city-victory |url-status=live}}</ref> On 27 August, he scored his first [[List of Premier League hat-tricks|Premier League hat-trick]] in a 4–2 win against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Palace]],<ref>{{cite web |date=27 August 2022 |title=Haaland's 19-minute Manchester City hat-trick puts out Crystal Palace's fire |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/27/manchester-city-crystal-palace-premier-league-match-report |access-date=27 August 2022 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922014633/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/27/manchester-city-crystal-palace-premier-league-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref> and recorded his second, a [[perfect hat-trick]],<ref>{{cite web |date=27 August 2022 |title=Erling Haaland scores perfect hat-trick against Nottingham Forest |url=https://www.skysports.com/watch/video/sports/football/12686519/haalands-perfect-hat-trick-flattens-forest |access-date=27 August 2022 |website=Sky Sports |archive-date=22 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220922004107/https://www.skysports.com/watch/video/sports/football/12686519/haalands-perfect-hat-trick-flattens-forest |url-status=live}}</ref> four days later in a 6–0 win against [[Nottingham Forest F.C.|Nottingham Forest]]. This made Haaland the fastest individual in Premier League history to score two hat-tricks, beating the previous record by 14 matches;<ref>{{cite web |date=31 August 2022 |title=Haaland scores hat-trick as Manchester City hit Nottingham Forest for six |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/31/manchester-city-nottingham-forest-premier-league-match-report|access-date=31 August 2022 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London|archive-date=20 September 2022|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220920171120/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/aug/31/manchester-city-nottingham-forest-premier-league-match-report|url-status=live}}</ref> he was later voted [[Premier League Player of the Month]] for August, his first month playing in the league.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/2787350 |title=Haaland voted August EA SPORTS Player of the Month |publisher=Premier League |date=16 September 2022 |access-date=23 January 2023}}</ref>

On 6 September, Haaland made his [[2022–23 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut for the club, getting a brace against Sevilla and becoming the first player to score 25 goals in their first 20 Champions League appearances.<ref>{{cite web |last=Sutcliffe |first=Steve |title=Sevilla 0–4 Manchester City: Erling Haaland scores twice in comfortable win for Pep Guardiola's side |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62800316 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=6 September 2022 |access-date=6 September 2022 |archive-date=5 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220905193634/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62800316 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Dawson |first=Rob |title=Erling Haaland, Man City's Champions League quest off to a flying start with big win over Sevilla |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-match/story/4740153/erling-haalandman-citys-champions-league-quest-off-to-a-flying-start-with-big-win-over-sevilla |work=ESPN |date=6 September 2022 |access-date=6 September 2022 |archive-date=26 September 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220926082227/https://www.espn.com/soccer/blog-the-match/story/4740153/erling-haalandman-citys-champions-league-quest-off-to-a-flying-start-with-big-win-over-sevilla |url-status=live}}</ref> He became the first player to score more than one goal on competition debut for three different clubs.<ref name=":6">{{Cite web |date=24 December 2023 |title=Erling Haaland in the Champions League: Records, stats, who he has scored against, how he compares to Mbappé, Ronaldo, Messi |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0268-11f9321e7599-fde3dd4a7bd0-1000--erling-haaland-in-the-champions-league-records-stats-who-h/ |access-date=23 January 2024 |publisher=[[UEFA]] |language=en}}</ref> In City's second group stage match a week later against his former club Borussia Dortmund, Haaland scored an acrobatic effort late in the contest to secure his side a 2–1 comeback victory.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |author-link= Phil McNulty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62894559 |title=Manchester City 2–1 Borussia Dortmund: Erling Haaland scores winner as hosts come from behind |date=14 September 2022 |access-date=14 September 2022 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> His winner was subsequently voted Champions League Goal of the Week by fans, and would later go on to be selected as the competition's Goal of the Season by UEFA's Technical Observer panel.<ref>{{cite news |date=15 September 2022 |access-date=15 September 2022 |title=Haaland strike wins Champions League Goal of the Week |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/haaland-champions-league-goal-of-the-week-63798837 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |date=1 July 2023 |title=2022/23 UEFA Champions League Goal of the Season: Erling Haaland tops Technical Observer selection |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0282-183b472dd4af-11ae8eda917e-1000--2022-23-uefa-champions-league-goal-of-the-season-erling-haal/ |access-date=1 July 2023 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref>

On 2 October, Haaland became the first player in Premier League history to score a hat-trick in three successive home matches during City's 6–3 [[Manchester derby|derby]] win against Manchester United, additionally earning two assists.<ref>{{cite magazine |last=Gastelum |first=Andrew |url=https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/10/02/erling-haaland-hat-trick-manchester-derby-city-foden-video |title=Man City's Erling Haaland, Phil Foden Net Hat Tricks in Manchester Derby |date=2 October 2022 |access-date=2 October 2022 |magazine=Sports Illustrated |archive-date=7 October 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221007014010/https://www.si.com/soccer/2022/10/02/erling-haaland-hat-trick-manchester-derby-city-foden-video |url-status=live}}</ref> He also became the quickest player in Premier League history to score three hat-tricks, doing so in eight league matches and surpassing the previous record of 48 set by [[Michael Owen]] in 1998, as well as halving [[Alan Shearer]]'s record of scoring three hat-tricks in a ten-match spell set during the [[1994–95 FA Premier League|1994–95 season]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Foster |first=Richard |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/oct/06/premier-league-records-erling-haaland-alan-shearer-andy-cole-sergio-aguero |title=Premier League records beware: Erling Haaland has landed |date=6 October 2022 |access-date=7 October 2022 |newspaper=The Guardian |location=London |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111811/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2022/oct/06/premier-league-records-erling-haaland-alan-shearer-andy-cole-sergio-aguero |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland's brace in City's 3–1 away win over Leeds United on 28 December took his tally to 20 goals in 14 league matches, becoming the fastest player in history to reach 20 Premier League goals and beating [[Sunderland A.F.C.|Sunderland]]'s [[Kevin Phillips (footballer)|Kevin Phillips]]' previous record by seven matches.<ref>{{cite web |last=Stone |first=Simon |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64113551 |title=Erling Haaland: Striker hungry for goals after missing out on World Cup |date=28 December 2022 |access-date=29 December 2022 |publisher=BBC Sport |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111818/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/64113551 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 January 2023, he scored a fourth hat-trick of the season against [[Wolverhampton Wanderers F.C.|Wolverhampton Wanderers]], giving him a total of 25 Premier League goals after just 19 matches; this surpassed the top scorers of the [[2021–22 Premier League|previous season]], [[Mohamed Salah]] and [[Son Heung-min]], who both scored 23 league goals across the entire campaign.<ref>{{cite news |last=Moses |first=Martin |date=22 January 2023 |title=Erling Haaland: Manchester City Star Breaks Last Season's Golden Boot Tally of Mohamed Salah, Heung Min Son |website=Sports Brief |url=https://sportsbrief.com/football/manchester-city/32916-erling-haaland-manchester-city-star-breaks-seasons-golden-boot-tally-mohamed-salah-heung-min-son/ |access-date=23 January 2023 |archive-date=1 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230401111334/https://sportsbrief.com/football/manchester-city/32916-erling-haaland-manchester-city-star-breaks-seasons-golden-boot-tally-mohamed-salah-heung-min-son/ |url-status=dead }}</ref>

On 14 March, Haaland scored five goals in a 7–0 round of 16 victory against RB Leipzig, tying [[Lionel Messi]] and [[Luiz Adriano]] for the most goals scored in a single Champions League match.<ref name=":4">{{cite web |last=Brown |first=Paul |date=15 March 2023 |title=Haaland breaks 94-year City goalscoring record |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-manchester-city-record-breaker-63814499 |access-date=2 September 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> He also set the new record for fastest time to score five goals in a Champions League match.<ref>{{Cite web |date=12 October 2023 |title=Manchester City 7–0 RB Leipzig (Mar 14, 2023) Game Analysis |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/report/_/gameId/656866 |access-date=23 January 2024 |work=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> In doing so, he reached 39 goals across all competitions, breaking [[Tommy Johnson (footballer, born 1901)|Tommy Johnson]]'s club record of 38 goals scored in a single season for City set in [[1928–29 Manchester City F.C. season|1928–29]].<ref name=":4" /> During City's [[2022–23 FA Cup|FA Cup]] quarter-final match against [[Burnley F.C.|Burnley]] four days later, Haaland scored his sixth hat-trick of the season, passing the 40-goal mark across all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=18 March 2023 |title=Haaland fires hat-trick as Manchester City demolish Kompany's Burnley 6–0 |work=[[The Guardian]] |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/18/manchester-city-burnley-fa-cup-quarter-final-match-report |access-date=21 May 2023 |archive-date=21 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230521101806/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/mar/18/manchester-city-burnley-fa-cup-quarter-final-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 11 April, Haaland scored the third goal of City's 3–0 Champions League win against Bayern Munich in the quarter-finals, his 45th goal of the season overall. This broke the previous record of 44 goals across all competitions in a season by a Premier League player held by Salah and [[Ruud van Nistelrooy]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Kelsey |first=George |title=Haaland surpasses long-standing Premier League goal record |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/Haaland%20surpasses%20long-standing%20Premier%20League%20goal%20record |access-date=12 April 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> Haaland registered two assists and a goal in his side's 4–1 home victory against league leaders [[Arsenal F.C.|Arsenal]] on 26 April, closing the gap between them and City in the table to just two points while the latter still had two matches in hand.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |author-link= Phil McNulty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65319949 |title=Manchester City 4–1 Arsenal: Kevin de Bruyne scores two and makes one in dominant display |date=26 April 2023 |access-date=26 April 2023 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> He would then score his 50th goal of the campaign across all competitions on 30 April against [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{Cite news |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=30 April 2023 |title=Haaland hits his 50th goal of the season |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-50-goals-manchester-city-63817773 |access-date=3 May 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> His six goals and two assists during April saw him win the league's Player of the Month for a second time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3331263 |title=Haaland wins EA SPORTS Player of the Month award |publisher=Premier League |date=12 May 2023 |access-date=12 May 2023}}</ref>

On 3 May, in City's return fixture against West Ham, Haaland scored his 35th league goal of the campaign, surpassing Shearer and [[Andy Cole]]'s joint record for the most goals scored in a single Premier League season.<ref name=":5">{{cite news |title=Haaland breaks Premier League goalscoring record |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-all-time-premier-league-goal-record-63818125 |access-date=3 May 2023 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |archive-date=3 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230503210621/https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-all-time-premier-league-goal-record-63818125 |url-status=live}}</ref> A week later, he was named [[FWA Footballer of the Year]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Erling Haaland named Football Writers' Association Men's Footballer of the Year for 2022/23; Chelsea's Sam Kerr wins Women's award |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12878888/erling-haaland-named-football-writers-association-mens-footballer-of-the-year-for-2022-23-chelseas-sam-kerr-wins-womens-award |archive-date=12 May 2023 |date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230512104715/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12878888/erling-haaland-named-football-writers-association-mens-footballer-of-the-year-for-2022-23-chelseas-sam-kerr-wins-womens-award |work=Sky Sports |location=UK}}</ref> He won by a record margin, earning 82% of the vote ahead of Arsenal's [[Bukayo Saka]] and [[Martin Ødegaard]] and becoming only the fourth player to claim the award in their debut season.<ref>{{cite news |date=12 May 2023 |title=Haaland wins FWA award by biggest margin ever |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/manchester-city-engman_city/story/4945971/haaland-wins-mens-fwa-footballer-of-the-year-award-by-record-margin-kerr-claims-womens-prize |access-date=12 May 2023 |work=ESPN |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512150219/https://www.espn.co.uk/football/manchester-city-engman_city/story/4945971/haaland-wins-mens-fwa-footballer-of-the-year-award-by-record-margin-kerr-claims-womens-prize |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=12 May 2023 |title=Haaland and Kerr win Football Writers' Association player of the year awards |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/12/haaland-and-kerr-win-football-writers-association-player-of-the-year-awards |access-date=12 May 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=12 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230512103419/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/12/haaland-and-kerr-win-football-writers-association-player-of-the-year-awards |url-status=live}}</ref> He would also go on to be voted [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]] by his colleagues in August.<ref name="PFA" /> Haaland won his first trophy with Manchester City after they clinched the 2022–23 Premier League title on 20 May.<ref>{{cite news |last=Unwin |first=Will |date=20 May 2023 |title=Manchester City win Premier League title for fifth time in six seasons |work=The Guardian |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/20/manchester-city-win-premier-league-title-for-fifth-time-in-six-seasons |access-date=20 May 2023 |issn=0261-3077 |archive-date=20 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230520192758/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/may/20/manchester-city-win-premier-league-title-for-fifth-time-in-six-seasons |url-status=live}}</ref> By assisting [[Phil Foden]]'s goal in a draw against [[Brighton & Hove Albion F.C.|Brighton & Hove Albion]] on 24 May, he reached 44 combined league goals and assists, thereby equalling [[Thierry Henry]]'s record for most total goal contributions in a 38-game Premier League season.<ref>{{cite web |last=Furniss |first=Matt |date=24 May 2023 |title=Most Goal Involvements in a Premier League Season |url=https://theanalyst.com/2023/05/most-goal-involvements-in-a-premier-league-season/ |access-date=24 May 2023 |website=The Analyst |archive-date=24 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230524232540/https://theanalyst.com/2023/05/most-goal-involvements-in-a-premier-league-season/ |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland's debut season in England earned him the [[Premier League Golden Boot]], after finishing as the league's top goalscorer, and the [[European Golden Shoe]], given to the top domestic scorer in Europe.<ref name="European Sports Magazines z432">{{cite web |title=The Golden Shoe |website=European Sports Magazines |url=https://www.eusm.eu/item/goldenshoe_winners.htm |access-date=25 June 2023 |archive-date=18 March 2022 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20220318235048/https://www.eusm.eu/item/goldenshoe_winners.htm |url-status=live}}</ref> With 36 goals in 35 appearances, he set the new record for highest number of goals scored in a Premier League season.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3486228 |title=Haaland claims 2022/23 Golden Boot |publisher=Premier League |date=28 May 2023 |access-date=1 June 2023 |archive-date=31 May 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230531140002/https://www.premierleague.com/news/3486228 |url-status=live}}</ref> With 52 goals in 53 appearances, Haaland also set the record for most goals by a Premier League player in all competitions in one season.<ref name=":7">{{Cite web |last=Tickner |first=Dave |date=20 December 2025 |title=Erling Haaland's ridiculous goalscoring stats at Manchester City and Norway |url=https://www.football365.com/news/erling-haaland-ridiculous-stats-half-decent-start-premier-league-life |access-date=2 March 2026 |website=Football365 |language=en}}</ref>

Haaland played the entirety of City's [[2023 FA Cup final|FA Cup final]] victory over Manchester United on 3 June, securing his second title with the club.<ref name="fa cup final 2023">{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65785637 |title=Manchester City 2–1 Manchester United |first=Phil |last=McNulty |author-link= Phil McNulty |publisher=BBC Sport |date=3 June 2023 |access-date=3 June 2023 |archive-date=2 June 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230602230358/https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/65785637 |url-status=live}}</ref> He then played another 90 minutes in the following week's [[2023 UEFA Champions League final|Champions League final]] against [[Inter Milan]]. Despite Haaland struggling to have a large impact on the match,<ref>{{cite news |last=Wright |first=Nick |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12897460/man-city-1-0-inter-milan-player-ratings-rodri-ruben-dias-excel-for-man-city-and-ederson-makes-crucial-saves |title=Man City 1–0 Inter Milan player ratings: Rodri, Ruben Dias excel for Man City and Ederson makes crucial saves |date=11 June 2023 |access-date=11 June 2023 |website=Sky Sports}}</ref> City would win 1–0 to earn a maiden Champions League title and achieve only the second-ever [[Treble (association football)#Continental trebles|continental treble]] by an English side.<ref>{{cite web |last=Dawkes |first=Phil |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65842717 |title=Manchester City: The big numbers behind the Treble |date=11 June 2023 |access-date=11 June 2023 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref> With 12 goals, Haaland finished as the top scorer of the Champions League season for a second time,<ref>{{cite news |date=9 June 2023 |title=Champions League top scorers 2022/23: Erling Haaland finishes top |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0279-160c8d06ee70-7766a7d071f5-1000--champions-league-top-scorers-2022-23-erling-haaland-finishe/ |access-date=9 June 2023 |publisher=UEFA}}</ref> joining Messi as the only players to accomplish this feat twice before turning 23.<ref>{{cite web |last=Menon |first=Anirudh |date=11 June 2023 |title=UCL Final Stats: Haaland joins Messi, Ronaldo as Guardiola and Man City create history |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/37833690/ucl-final-stats-haaland-joins-messi-ronaldo-guardiola-man-city-create-history |access-date=2 September 2023 |work=ESPN}}</ref> Haaland would be subsequently named the [[UEFA Men's Player of the Year Award|UEFA Men's Player of the Year]] in August, ahead of Messi and Manchester City teammate [[Kevin De Bruyne]].<ref name="UMP23" /><ref>{{cite news |date=17 August 2023 |title=2022/23 UEFA Men's Player of the Year award nominees announced: Kevin De Bruyne, Erling Haaland, Lionel Messi |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0284-18c1b70cc3e6-ccc3c4cc0186-1000--2022-23-uefa-men-s-player-of-the-year-award-nominees-announc/ |access-date=21 August 2023 |publisher=UEFA |archive-date=20 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230820001136/https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/0284-18c1b70cc3e6-ccc3c4cc0186-1000--2022-23-uefa-men-s-player-of-the-year-award-nominees-announc/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

====2023–24: Second consecutive Premier League Golden Boot====
[[File:Erling Haaland 2023 (cropped-v2).jpg|thumb|upright|Haaland with Manchester City in 2023]]

Manchester City began their [[2023–24 Premier League]] season on 11 August 2023, with Haaland scoring a brace in a 3–0 away win against newly promoted team Burnley.<ref>{{cite web |last=McNulty |first=Phil |author-link= Phil McNulty |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/66402155 |title=Burnley 0–3 Manchester City: Erling Haaland scores twice in opening win |publisher=BBC Sport |date=11 August 2023 |url-status=live |access-date=11 August 2023 |archive-date=11 August 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230811212641/https://www.bbc.com/sport/live/football/65928386}}</ref> Just days later, Haaland would win his first trophy of the season following City's victory over [[2022–23 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] winners [[Sevilla FC|Sevilla]] in the [[2023 UEFA Super Cup|UEFA Super Cup]]; although not scoring during the match, he did convert the first penalty in the [[Penalty shoot-out (association football)|shoot-out]] following the end of regulation.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2023/aug/16/manchester-city-sevilla-uefa-super-cup-match-report |title=Manchester City secure Uefa Super Cup with shootout win over Sevilla |newspaper=The Guardian |date=16 August 2023|access-date=16 August 2023}}</ref> On 29 August, Haaland was named the [[PFA Players' Player of the Year]],<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2023/8/29/pfa-players-player-of-the-year-erling-haaland |title=Erling Haaland: PFA Players' Player of the Year |publisher=PFA |date=29 August 2023 |access-date=30 August 2023}}</ref> having earlier been included in the [[PFA Team of the Year]] for the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.thepfa.com/news/2023/8/29/pfa-premier-league-team-of-the-year-2023 |title=PFA Premier League Team of the Year |publisher=PFA |date=29 August 2023 |access-date=30 August 2023}}</ref>

With his first three goals of the season, Haaland became the fastest player to reach 100 league goals in [[Big Five (association football)|Europe's top 5 leagues]], accomplishing the feat in just 103 appearances, surpassing the previous record of 100 goals in 133 appearances set by [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]].<ref>{{Cite tweet |number=1690087005571461120 |user=BeSoccer_Pro |title=Erling Haaland llega a los 100 goles en las grandes ligas. Es el que ha necesitado menos partidos para ello |date=11 August 2023 |access-date=17 September 2024}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Brajkovic |first=Josip |date=12 September 2023 |title=Fastest players in the top five leagues to reach 100 goals |url=https://www.insidesport.com/c/legends/fastest-players-in-the-top-five-leagues-to-reach-100-goals/4051 |access-date=18 September 2024 |website=InsideSport.com |language=en-US}}</ref>

After registering a seventh club hat-trick plus an assist against Fulham on 2 September, Haaland became the fastest ever player to achieve 50 Premier League goal involvements (goals plus assists); with just 39 appearances in the competition, he eclipsed Andy Cole's previous record by four matches.<ref>{{cite news |date=2 September 2023 |title=Haaland makes more Premier League history |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/3666939 |access-date=2 September 2023 |publisher=Premier League}}</ref> On 25 October, Haaland scored his first two [[2023–24 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] goals of the season in a 3–1 win at [[BSC Young Boys|Young Boys]]. On 29 October, he recorded two goals and one assist in a 3–0 derby win over Manchester United at [[Old Trafford]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/26806/12992912/man-utd-0-3-man-city-erling-haaland-and-phil-foden-on-target-as-pep-guardiolas-side-win-manchester-derby-in-style |title=Man Utd 0–3 Man City: Erling Haaland and Phil Foden on target as Pep Guardiola's side win Manchester derby in style |date=30 October 2023|access-date=30 October 2023 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> The following day, he was presented with the [[Gerd Müller Trophy]] at the [[2023 Ballon d'Or]] awards ceremony, given to the player with the most goals scored for club and country across a single season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/ballon-d-or/2023/ballon-dor-2023-it-s-what-i-m-good-at-erling-haaland-on-his-job-to-score-after-picking-up-award_sto9862597/story.shtml |title=Ballon d'Or 2023: 'It's what I'm good at' – Erling Haaland on 'his job' to score after picking up award |date=30 October 2023 |website=Eurosport}}</ref> On 25 November, Haaland became the fastest player to score 50 Premier League goals in a 1–1 draw with Liverpool; with just 48 appearances, he comfortably beat the previous record of 65 matches by Andy Cole.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Smith |first1=Emma |title=Erling Haaland: Manchester City striker makes Premier League history against Liverpool |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/67531278 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=25 November 2023 |date=25 November 2023}}</ref> After suffering a [[Stress fracture|bone stress injury]] in his foot in early December, Haaland would miss nearly two months of action, including City's success at the [[2023 FIFA Club World Cup]], and would not return to the pitch until the end of January 2024.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://apnews.com/article/erling-haaland-man-city-guardiola-b96fce3ba59ac4780f29a3209fce9359 |title=Haaland to return for Man City after nearly 2 months out with foot injury |work=Associated Press News |date=30 January 2024|access-date=31 January 2024}}</ref>

On 20 February 2024, Haaland scored the sole goal of a home win over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]], joining [[Harry Kane]] as the only players to have scored against every Premier League team they had faced.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Mukherjee |first1=Soham |title=Erling Haaland sets another record! Man City superstar completes Premier League feat only previously accomplished by Harry Kane following Brentford winner |url=https://www.goal.com/en-ae/lists/erling-haaland-record-man-city-premier-league-feat-harry-kane-brentford-winner/blt8747a5a66ca84682 |website=Goal (website) |access-date=21 February 2024 |date=20 February 2024}}</ref> A week later, he netted five goals in a 6–2 victory against [[Luton Town F.C.|Luton Town]] in the [[2023–24 FA Cup|FA Cup]], marking the second time he achieved such a feat for the club and becoming the first player to do so twice.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/68417647 |title=Luton Town 2–6 Manchester City: Erling Haaland scores five as holders romp into quarter-final |publisher=BBC Sport |date=27 February 2024 |access-date=27 February 2024}}</ref> Additionally, he matched his club's record for most goals by an individual in an FA Cup match, a record previously held by [[Frank Roberts (footballer, born 1893)|Frank Roberts]] in 1926 and [[Bobby Marshall (footballer, born 1903)|Bobby Marshall]] in 1930. Furthermore, Haaland's accomplishment marked the first instance of a player scoring five goals in the competition since [[George Best]] in 1970.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-club-record-63844671 |title=Haaland's five goal haul equals City FA Cup scoring record |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=27 February 2024 |access-date=27 February 2024}}</ref>{{Overly detailed inline|date=February 2026}} On 4 May, Haaland scored four goals in a 5–1 win over Wolverhampton Wanderers, his first league hat-trick of the year and third of the season in all competitions.<ref>{{cite news |last=Bray |first=Joe |date=4 May 2024 |title=Man City vs Wolves highlights and reaction as Haaland hits four in Premier League stroll |url=https://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/man-city-vs-wolves-live-29107190 |access-date=4 May 2024 |work=[[Manchester Evening News]]}}</ref>

Haaland scored both goals in City's 2–0 vital win away to [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]] on 14 May, bringing his side back to the top of the Premier League table with one match remaining.<ref>{{cite news |date=14 May 2024 |title=Haaland double takes Man City top ahead of final day |url=https://www.premierleague.com/news/4008826 |access-date=14 May 2024 |publisher=Premier League}}</ref> Five days later, City would successfully defend their title following a 3–1 victory against West Ham.<ref>{{cite news |last=Gillespie |first=Tom |url=https://news.sky.com/story/manchester-city-win-record-breaking-fourth-premier-league-title-in-a-row-13139671 |title=Manchester City win record-breaking fourth Premier League title in a row |publisher=Sky News |date=19 May 2024|access-date=19 May 2024}}</ref> Haaland also secured a second consecutive Premier League Golden Boot, with 27 goals in 31 matches.<ref>{{cite news |last=Myson |first=Chris |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-my/football/premier-league/articles/man-city-star-haaland-wins-premier-league-golden-boot-again-2024-05-19 |title=Man City star Haaland wins Premier League Golden Boot again |publisher=beIN Sports |date=19 May 2024|access-date=19 May 2024}}</ref> However, he would be unable to retain the FA Cup, failing to score in City's 2–1 [[2024 FA Cup final|final rematch]] defeat to Manchester United on 25 May.<ref>{{cite news |last=Leigh |first=Neil |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-manchester-united-2024-fa-cup-final-report-63852241 |title=City suffer FA Cup final disappointment |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=25 May 2024|access-date=25 May 2024}}</ref>

====2024–25: Further goalscoring records====
[[File:ManCity20240722-031 (cropped).jpg|thumb|upright|Haaland with Manchester City in 2024]]

After failing to score in City's opening [[2024 FA Community Shield|2024 Community Shield]] victory over [[Manchester United F.C.|Manchester United]], but having successfully converted his penalty in the shoot-out, Haaland scored the club's first goal of the league season in a 2–0 victory at [[Chelsea F.C.|Chelsea]] on 18 August 2024, in what was his 100th appearance for City.<ref>{{cite news |last=Stone |first=Simon |date=10 August 2024 |title=Man Utd 1–1 Man City |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c9wjkjyqpg4t |access-date=27 August 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last=Smith |first=Jonathan |date=18 August 2024 |title=Haaland strikes on 100th appearance as City kick of Premier League in style |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/chelsea-v-man-city-match-report-august-18-63859590 |access-date=27 August 2024 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> On 25 August, Haaland netted his first hat-trick of the season with the help of a penalty in a 4–1 victory against newly promoted [[Ipswich Town F.C.|Ipswich Town]], his seventh Premier League hat-trick.<ref>{{cite news |date=25 August 2024 |title=Man City 4–1 Ipswich Town: Erling Haaland hat-trick puts Town to the sword after early shock |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11661/13200584/man-city-4-1-ipswich-town-erling-haaland-hat-trick-puts-town-to-the-sword |access-date=27 August 2024 |publisher=Sky Sports}}</ref> In the following match on 31 August against [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]], he recorded another hat-trick in a 3–1 away victory, tying Harry Kane as the active player with the most Premier League hat-tricks, with eight. Haaland's hat-trick against the ''Hammers'' also allowed Manchester City to surpass Liverpool as the club with the most hat-tricks in the Premier League.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Ibarra |first1=Diego Mayel |last2=Roche |first2=Calum |date=31 August 2024 |title=How many hat-tricks has Haaland scored in the Premier League? Where is he on all-time list? |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/how-many-hat-tricks-has-haaland-scored-in-the-premier-league-where-is-he-on-all-time-list-n/ |access-date=31 August 2024 |work=Diario AS}}</ref> Haaland's seven goals after three matches broke the record of six set by former City player [[Edin Džeko]], for the most goals in the first three Premier League matches of a season; he also became the first player to score two hat-tricks in a team's first three league matches since [[Paul Jewell]] of [[Bradford City A.F.C.|Bradford City]] in the [[1994–95 Football League#Second Division|1994–95 season]].<ref>{{cite news |last=Leigh |first=Neil |date=31 August 2024 |title=Back-to-back Haaland treble maintains City's perfect start |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/west-ham-v-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report-1-63860714 |access-date=2 September 2024 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> On 14 September, Haaland scored another two goals in a 2–1 victory over [[Brentford F.C.|Brentford]], eclipsing [[Wayne Rooney]]'s record tally of eight goals in the first four matches of a Premier League season achieved with Manchester United in the [[2011–12 Premier League|2011–12 season]], after only deciding to play the day before following the death of a close family friend.<ref>{{cite news |last=Jackson |first=Jamie |date=14 September 2024 |title=Erling Haaland double sinks Brentford after Yoane Wissa jolts Manchester City |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2024/sep/14/manchester-city-brentford-premier-league-match-report |access-date=14 September 2024 |work=The Guardian}}</ref> On 22 September, Haaland matched [[Cristiano Ronaldo]]'s record of reaching 100 goals across all competitions for one club in 105 appearances in [[Big Five (association football)|Europe's top five leagues]], when he scored the opener in a 2–2 draw against Arsenal.<ref>{{cite news |date=22 September 2024 |title=Haaland nets 100th City goal; ties Ronaldo record |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/41301639/erling-haaland-100th-man-city-goal-cristiano-ronaldo-record |access-date=22 September 2024 |work=ESPN}}</ref>

On 17 January 2025, Haaland signed to extend his contract with the club until 2034, while his previous deal was due to expire in 2027.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-10-year-manchester-city-contract-63872694 |title=Here To Stay: Haaland signs new 10-year City contract! |last=Leigh |first=Neil |date=17 January 2025 |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |access-date=17 January 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/football/2025/01/17/erling-haaland-signs-nine-year-contract-extension-man-city |title=Erling Haaland signs nine-and-a-half-year contract extension at Manchester City |last=Ducker |first=James |date=17 January 2025 |newspaper=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |access-date=17 January 2025}}</ref> The deal is the longest in Premier League history, with Haaland reportedly earning £500,000 per week with this new agreement.<ref>{{cite news |date=17 January 2025 |title=Erling Haaland signs lucrative new contract with Man City until 2034 |url=https://apnews.com/article/erling-haaland-man-city-contract-4d1b185ac111ae32b6b5884f4ef19641 |access-date=19 January 2025 |website=AP News}}</ref> Following former club captain [[Kyle Walker]]'s loan departure, Haaland was nominated to take up the captaincy by manager [[Pep Guardiola]]. He debuted as captain on 15 February, in a 4–0 win over [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Guardiola: I nominated Erling as a captain |url=https://www.mancity.com/citytv/mens/manchester-city-4-0-newcastle-pep-guardiola-reaction-63875239 |date=15 February 2025 |access-date=15 February 2025 |publisher=Manchester City F.C.}}</ref> After scoring against Brighton & Hove Albion on 15 March, Haaland overtook Alan Shearer to become the fastest player to reach 100 goal involvements in the Premier League, doing so in 94 matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/articles/c8rk16vyrzmo|title=Haaland reaches 100 goal involvements in record time|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Emlyn|last=Begley|date=15 March 2025|access-date=19 March 2025}}</ref> During City's [[2024–25 FA Cup|FA Cup]] quarter-final match against [[AFC Bournemouth|Bournemouth]], Haaland battled for the ball with [[Lewis Cook (footballer, born 1997)|Lewis Cook]], and ended up colliding into the electronic advertising boards.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c07z3l1g2p4t|title=AFC Bournemouth 1–2 Manchester City|publisher=BBC Sport|first=Phil|last=McNulty|author-link=Phil McNulty|date=30 March 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> This resulted in him injuring his ankle and missing a number of matches, making his return on 10 May in a goalless draw against already relegated [[Southampton F.C.|Southampton]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/c7932yjgwrgt|title=Southampton 0–0 Manchester City|first=Tom|last=Rostance|date=10 May 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> On 17 May, in the [[2025 FA Cup final|FA Cup final]] against [[Crystal Palace F.C.|Crystal Place]], Haaland turned down the opportunity to take a penalty, instead handing the ball to [[Omar Marmoush]], whose effort was saved by [[Dean Henderson]]. At the time, City were losing 1–0, and Palace would see the game out in the second half to win the first ever trophy in their history.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cm23zrkn7ryt|title=Crystal Palace 1–0 Manchester City|first=Phil|last=McNulty|author-link=Phil McNulty|date=17 May 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref> Haaland finished the Premier League season with 22 goals, behind Mohamed Salah and [[Alexander Isak]], scoring on the final day in a 2–0 win over [[Fulham F.C.|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/live/cjdzzrkd9vgt|title=Fulham 0–2 Manchester City|first=Shamoon|last=Hafez|date=25 May 2025|access-date=16 July 2025}}</ref>

On 26 June, Haaland scored his 300th career goal in a 5–2 win over [[Juventus FC|Juventus]] in a [[2025 FIFA Club World Cup|FIFA Club World Cup]] group stage match, becoming, at the age of 24 years and 340 days, the second-youngest player in the 21st century to reach the landmark, only behind [[Kylian Mbappé]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jun/26/juventus-manchester-city-club-world-cup-match-report |title=Erling Haaland hits 300th goal in Manchester City rout of Juventus at Club World Cup |newspaper=The Guardian |date=26 June 2025 |access-date=28 June 2025 |archive-date=27 June 2025 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20250627122554/https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/jun/26/juventus-manchester-city-club-world-cup-match-report |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4455 |title=Haaland, 2nd youngest to reach 300 goals in XXI century |publisher=[[IFFHS]] |date=27 June 2025 |access-date=2 July 2025 }}</ref> In the following match on 30 June, he scored again in a 4–3 loss to [[Al Hilal SFC|Al Hilal]] in the round of 16, matching [[Lionel Messi]]'s record for most goals in official international club competitions before the age of 25 (both at 56).<ref>{{cite web |url=https://iffhs.com/posts/4464 |title=Club World Cup statistics (Round of 16, 30 June – 1 July) |publisher=[[IFFHS]] |date=1 July 2025 |access-date=2 July 2025 }}</ref>

====2025–26: Third Golden Boot and 100th Premier League goal====
On 16 August 2025, Haaland scored a brace in City's first match of the [[2025–26 Premier League]], helping his team to a 4–0 away victory against Wolverhampton Wanderers.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hafez |first=Shamoon |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c2077030850t |title=Wolves 0–4 Man City: Reijnders and Haaland shine as Man City thrash Wolves |website=BBC Sport |date=16 August 2025 |access-date=16 August 2025}}</ref> On 31 August, Haaland scored against Brighton & Hove Albion, and became the player with the most goals (88) in his first 100 matches in the Premier League, surpassing Alan Shearer's record of 79 goals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-100-premier-league-appearances-record-63892266 |title=Haaland sets goalscoring standard after 100 Premier League appearances |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=31 August 2025 |access-date=1 September 2025}}</ref> On 14 September, he scored a brace in City's 3–0 home win in the Manchester derby.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-manchester-united-14-september-63893464 |title=Derby delight for City after Foden strike and Haaland double |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=14 September 2025 |access-date=14 September 2025}}</ref> Four days later, he scored the first goal in City's opening match in the [[2025–26 UEFA Champions League]], a 2–0 home victory against [[SSC Napoli|Napoli]], becoming the fastest player to reach 50 goals in the competition, having done so in only 49 matches.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/manchester-city-v-napoli-champions-league-report-63893814 |title=Record-breaking Haaland and Doku fire impressive City to victory over Napoli |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=18 September 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.mancity.com/news/mens/erling-haaland-becomes-quickest-to-50-champions-league-goals-63893823 |title=Haaland becomes quickest to 50 Champions League goals |publisher=Manchester City F.C. |date=18 September 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/news/027d-170b3182d9ed-587169daf860-1000--champions-league-goalscoring-milestones-erling-haaland-quic/ |title=Champions League goalscoring milestones: Erling Haaland quickest to 50 |publisher=UEFA |date=18 September 2025 |access-date=19 September 2025}}</ref> On 2 December, Haaland became the fastest player to reach [[List of footballers with 100 or more Premier League goals|100 goals in the Premier League]], scoring in a 5–4 away win over Fulham.<ref>{{cite web |last=MacInnes |first=Paul |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2025/dec/02/fulham-manchester-city-premier-league-match-report |title=Manchester City hold off heroic Fulham fightback to win nine-goal epic |work=The Guardian |date=2 December 2025 }}</ref> He achieved the milestone in just 111 appearances, surpassing Alan Shearer's 1995 record set after 124 matches.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 December 2025 |title=Man City's Erling Haaland breaks Alan Shearer record with 100th goal |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/47051666/manchester-city-erling-haaland-alan-shearer-premier-league-100-goal-record |access-date=2 December 2025 |website=ESPN.com |language=en}}</ref> On 8 February 2026, he converted a stoppage-time penalty in a 2–1 away victory over Liverpool, securing his club's first league double over them since the 1936–37 season.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/live-blogs/liverpool-vs-manchester-city-live-updates-premier-league-score-result/3I23E8x5PczK/SdJhYhPdWOWB/ |title=How Manchester City secured dramatic late comeback win against Liverpool to go six points off Arsenal |date=8 February 2026 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-04-19 |title=Man City player ratings vs Arsenal: Erling Haaland has his revenge! Star striker turns Premier League title race on its head while Rayan Cherki dazzles as Gigi Donnarumma disaster goes unpunished {{!}} Goal.com India |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/man-city-player-ratings-vs-arsenal-erling-haaland-rayan-cherki-gigi-donnarumma/blt4451bac098362730 |access-date=2026-04-20 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-IN}}</ref> He concluded the season with 27 goals, securing his third Golden Boot award and matching the tally of both Harry Kane and Alan Shearer.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en-sa/lists/man-city-star-erling-haaland-wins-third-golden-boot-to-equal-harry-kane-and-alan-shearer-in-premier-league-record-books/blt0d855e827855b702 |title=Man City star Erling Haaland wins THIRD Golden Boot to equal Harry Kane & Alan Shearer in Premier League record books |publisher=Goal.com |date=24 May 2026 }}</ref>

== International career ==

===2015–2018: Youth level===
Haaland plays for Norway, and has represented them at various age groups. On 27 March 2018, while with the [[Norway national under-19 football team|Norway under-19 side]],<ref>{{cite web |title=UEFA European Under-19 Championship |publisher=UEFA |date=10 May 2018 |access-date=10 May 2018 |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/teams/players/250103758--erling-haaland/ |archive-date=10 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180510184715/https://www.uefa.com/under19/season=2018/teams/player=250103758/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref> Haaland scored a hat-trick against [[Scotland national under-19 football team|Scotland]] in a 5–4 victory, helping his country secure qualification to the [[2018 UEFA European Under-19 Championship]].<ref>{{cite news |title=Scotland U19s miss out on Euro 2019 qualification after incredible defeat to Norway |newspaper=Daily Record |date=27 March 2018 |access-date=27 March 2018 |url=https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/scotland-u19s-miss-out-euro-12261449 |archive-date=11 May 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180511012552/https://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/sport/football/football-news/scotland-u19s-miss-out-euro-12261449 |url-status=live}}</ref> On 22 July 2018, Haaland scored a penalty against [[Italy national under-19 football team|Italy]] in a 1–1 draw during the tournament finals.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Kean fires Italy level after Håland's penalty |publisher=UEFA |date=22 July 2018 |access-date=24 July 2018 |url=https://www.uefa.com/under19/match/2024504--italy-vs-norway/ |archive-date=24 July 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180724035755/https://www.uefa.com/under19/season=2018/matches/round=2000837/match=2024504/index.html |url-status=live}}</ref> On 30 May 2019, Haaland scored nine goals in the [[Norway national under-20 football team|Norway under-20 team]]'s 12–0 win against [[Honduras national under-20 football team|Honduras]] at the [[2019 FIFA U-20 World Cup]] in [[Lublin]], Poland.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48465037 |title=Erling Braut Haaland: Norway player scores nine goals in U20 World Cup win |date=30 May 2019 |publisher=BBC Sport |access-date=28 August 2019 |archive-date=18 July 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190718121332/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/48465037 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/match/400010584/#cesar-romero-and-luis-palma-of-honduras-arrive |title=Nine-goal Haland and Norway make history |date=30 May 2019 |publisher=FIFA |access-date=31 May 2019 |archive-date=17 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190517053718/https://www.fifa.com/u20worldcup/matches/match/400010584/#cesar-romero-and-luis-palma-of-honduras-arrive |url-status=dead}}</ref> This was Norway's biggest ever win at U-20 level, as well as Honduras' heaviest ever defeat. Haaland also set a new U-20 World Cup record for most goals scored by a single player in a match, with the result additionally being the biggest win by any team in the history of the tournament.<ref name="NorwayRecord">{{cite web |url=https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/fifa-u20-world-cup/1109030/fifa-u-20-world-cup-2019-erling-haaland-scores-record-triple-hat-trick-as-norway-thrash-honduras-12-0/ |title=FIFA U-20 World Cup 2019: Erling Haaland scores record triple hat-trick as Norway thrash Honduras 12–0 |date=31 May 2019 |access-date=31 May 2019 |website=Fox Sports Asia |archive-date=31 May 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190531011707/https://www.foxsportsasia.com/football/fifa-u20-world-cup/1109030/fifa-u-20-world-cup-2019-erling-haaland-scores-record-triple-hat-trick-as-norway-thrash-honduras-12-0/ |url-status=dead}}</ref> Despite the Norwegians being eliminated in the group stage, and Haaland not scoring in any other matches at the tournament, he still won the [[FIFA U-20 World Cup awards#Golden Boot|Golden Boot]] as the competition's top scorer.<ref name="golden" />

===2019–2021: Senior debut and first major tournament===
Born in Leeds, Haaland was eligible to play for [[England national football team|England]], but only wished to play for Norway according to coach [[Gareth Southgate]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/erling-haaland-england-eligible-euro-2020-norway-dortmund-gareth-southgate-a9562321.html |title=Southgate explains why Haaland England call-up was never likely |website=The Independent|date=13 June 2020|access-date=23 November 2022|archive-date=23 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221123223412/https://www.independent.co.uk/sport/football/international/erling-haaland-england-eligible-euro-2020-norway-dortmund-gareth-southgate-a9562321.html |url-status=live}}</ref>

On 28 August 2019, Haaland was named by manager [[Lars Lagerbäck]] to the [[Norway national football team|Norway senior team]] squad to face [[Malta national football team|Malta]] and [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] in [[UEFA Euro 2020 qualifying]] matches, debuting on 5 September 2019 against the former opponent.<ref>{{Cite news|first=Gianluca|last=Lia|title=Champions League top scorer Haaland named in Norway squad for Malta game|url=https://timesofmalta.com/article/champions-league-top-scorer-haaland-named-in-norway-squad-for-malta.748722|newspaper=[[The Times (Malta)]]|date=9 November 2019|access-date=2 October 2024}}</ref> On 4 September 2020, Haaland scored his first senior international goal for Norway in a 1–2 loss against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in the [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League B]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Erling Braut Haaland scores but Norway lose to Austria|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54035331|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=4 September 2020|access-date=2 October 2024}}</ref> Three days later, he scored a brace in a 5–1 victory against [[Northern Ireland national football team|Northern Ireland]].<ref>{{cite news|first=Andy|last=Hunter|title=Northern Ireland humbled at home by Erling Braut Haaland-inspired Norway|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2020/sep/07/northern-ireland-norway-nations-league-match-report|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|date=13 June 2020|access-date=23 November 2022}}</ref>

On 11 October, Haaland scored his first international hat-trick in Norway's 4–0 victory over [[Romania national football team|Romania]] in a Nations League B match, bringing his tally for the senior team to six goals in six matches played.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54479918 |title=Norway 4–0 Romania: Erling Braut Haaland scores a hat-trick for hosts|publisher=BBC Sport|date=11 October 2020 |access-date=11 October 2020 |archive-date=19 October 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201019075648/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/54479918 |url-status=live}}</ref>

===2021–2024: Consecutive Nations League top scorer and all-time Norway top scorer===
[[File:Norway Italy - June 2025 C 21.jpg|thumb|upright|Haaland celebrating a goal with [[Norway national football team|Norway]] in 2025]]

During the September 2021 international break, Haaland scored five goals in three [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualification]] matches, including a second hat-trick for Norway in a 5–1 victory against [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58461066 |title=Norway 5–1 Gibraltar: Erling Braut Haaland scores hat-trick |publisher=BBC Sport|date=7 September 2021 |access-date=8 September 2021 |archive-date=7 September 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210907211921/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/58461066 |url-status=live}}</ref> With six goals in [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League B#Group 4|League B]] between June and September 2022, he finished as the joint-top scorer of the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]].<ref name="UNL23" />

Haaland's brace in a [[UEFA Euro 2024 qualifying|Euro 2024 qualifier]] against [[Cyprus national football team|Cyprus]] on 12 October 2023 brought his international tally to 27 goals in 27 appearances, surpassing [[Einar Gundersen]] as Norway's second-highest all-time top scorer.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.football365.com/news/erling-haaland-ridiculous-stats-half-decent-start-premier-league-life |title=The ridiculous stats of Erling Haaland: Long-standing Norway record next in striker's sights |website=Football365 |date=13 October 2023 |access-date=13 October 2023}}</ref> On 5 June 2024, Haaland scored a third hat-trick for his country in a 3–0 [[Exhibition game#Association football|friendly]] win against [[Kosovo national football team|Kosovo]], bringing him within three goals of Norwegian top scorer [[Jørgen Juve]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/erling-haaland-scores-a-hat-trick-as-norway-beat-kosovo-in-friendly-to-end-winless-streak-in-2024_sto20009264/story.shtml |title=Erling Haaland nets hat-trick in convincing win over Kosovo, closes in on Norway all-time record|website=[[Eurosport]]|publisher=[[TNT Sports International]]|date=5 June 2024 |access-date=5 June 2024}}</ref>

On 10 October 2024, Haaland scored a brace in a 3–0 [[2024–25 UEFA Nations League B|Nations League]] win over [[Slovenia national football team|Slovenia]], reaching 34 international goals to become Norway's [[List of international goals scored by Erling Haaland|all-time top scorer]] at the age of just 24, and overtaking Juve's record that had stood since 1937.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/41721566/erling-haaland-norway-leading-scorer |title=Erling Haaland becomes Norway's all-time leading scorer |work=ESPN |date=10 October 2024 |access-date=10 October 2024}}</ref> On 17 November, he recorded a fourth international hat-trick in a 5–0 win against [[Kazakhstan national football team|Kazakhstan]], helping Norway clinch promotion to [[2026–27 UEFA Nations League A|League A]] of the Nations League for the first time.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/live/c74lxgzw0yqt |title=Norway 5–0 Kazakhstan: Erling Haaland scores hat-trick to seal promotion |publisher=BBC Sport |date=17 November 2024 |access-date=17 November 2024}}</ref>

===2025–present: First World Cup===
On 6 June 2025, Haaland scored Norway's final goal in their 3–0 [[2026 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|World Cup qualifying]] win against [[Italy national football team|Italy]], securing the nation's first victory over the Italians in 25 years.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.foxsports.com/stories/soccer/world-cup-qualifying-haaland-leads-norway-its-first-win-vs-italy-25-years |title=World Cup qualifying: Haaland leads Norway to its first win vs. Italy in 25 years |publisher=Fox Sports |date=12 June 2025 |access-date=12 June 2025}}</ref> On 9 September, he scored five goals and assisted a further two in an 11–1 win over [[Moldova national football team|Moldova]], becoming the first male European player to record five goals in a World Cup qualifier since [[Hans Krankl]] in 1977.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/story/_/id/46208975/erling-haaland-scores-5-norway-keep-pressure-italy |title=Erling Haaland scores 5 as Norway keep pressure on Italy |work=ESPN |date=9 September 2025 |access-date=9 September 2025}}</ref> A month later, on 11 October, he scored a hat-trick in a 5–0 win over [[Israel national football team|Israel]], becoming the fastest player to reach [[List of men's footballers with 50 or more international goals|50 international goals]], breaking [[Harry Kane]]'s record by achieving the milestone in just 46 matches compared to Kane's 71.<ref>{{cite web |last=Stewart |first=Ben |url=https://www.planetfootball.com/manchester-city/erling-haaland-obliterates-goalscoring-record-harry-kane-neymar |title=Erling Haaland obliterates goalscoring record once held by Harry Kane & Neymar |publisher=Planet Football |date=12 October 2025 |access-date=12 October 2025}}</ref> On 16 November, he scored twice in a 4–1 away win over Italy, securing his nation's place at the [[2026 FIFA World Cup]] with eight victories, marking their first World Cup appearance since [[1998 FIFA World Cup|1998]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Begley |first=Emlyn |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cpv18vznj78o |title=How Haaland fired Norway to the World Cup |publisher=BBC Sport |date=16 November 2025 |access-date=16 November 2025}}</ref> Haaland finished the World Cup qualifying campaign with 16 goals, scoring in all eight of Norway's matches, and equalling [[Robert Lewandowski]]'s record tally from the qualifiers for [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.beinsports.com/en-us/soccer/uefa-world-cup-qualifiers/articles/italy-1-4-norway-haaland-double-caps-world-cup-qualification-in-style-2025-11-16 |title=Italy 1–4 Norway: Haaland double caps World Cup qualification in style |publisher=beIN SPORTS |date=16 November 2025 |access-date=16 November 2025}}</ref> He also matched [[Abdul Ghani Minhat]]'s feat of scoring in 11 consecutive international appearances, achieved back in 1962.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/ca/soccer/news/erling-haaland-consecutive-goals-record-international-football/864cf4abdba8c55afb7ee48a |title=Erling Haaland equals consecutive goals record held for over 60 years which neither Messi nor Ronaldo could touch |website=Sporting News |date=16 November 2025 |access-date=16 November 2025}}</ref>

== Player profile ==
=== Style of play ===
A prolific goalscorer who has been regarded as one of the leading players of his generation, Haaland is often described as a complete [[Forward (association football)#Centre-forward|centre forward]].<ref name="Ogden 2022">{{cite web |last=Ogden |first=Mark |title=Haaland is the best player in the world, and Man City should blow past everyone |work=ESPN |date=2 October 2022 |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/manchester-city-engman_city/story/4759976/haaland-is-the-worlds-best-player-and-man-city-are-unbeatable |access-date=4 April 2023 |archive-date=4 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230404054327/https://www.espn.com/soccer/manchester-city-engman_city/story/4759976/haaland-is-the-worlds-best-player-and-man-city-are-unbeatable |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=The 100 best male footballers in the world 2022 |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/jan/24/the-100-best-male-footballers-in-the-world-2022 |access-date=7 February 2023 |website=The Guardian |date=27 January 2023 |archive-date=22 March 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230322115802/https://www.theguardian.com/football/ng-interactive/2023/jan/24/the-100-best-male-footballers-in-the-world-2022 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="Top 50 Best Players">{{Cite web |title=Top 50 Best Players |url=https://www.footballcritic.com/top-players |access-date=7 February 2023 |website=FootballCritic |archive-date=7 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230207073751/https://www.footballcritic.com/top-players |url-status=live}}</ref> He uses his sizeable frame to hold play up effectively and involve others. He has the pace and clever movement to run in behind, he can dribble and create, and he can finish with both feet and his head. He usually comes deep to collect the ball to help his team build play, often looking to spread the ball wide for a teammate, before turning and sprinting towards goal. He sometimes comes too deep for the defenders to follow him; as such he has the awareness to turn on the ball and create from a forward-facing position. In the [[penalty area]] he makes small, sharp movements to spot an opportunity for a teammate to attempt to find him in space, and can change the line on which he is running and accelerate into that space, making him extremely difficult for defenders to read.<ref name=SOP1>{{cite web |url=https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/erling-haaland-manchester-city-borussia-dortmund/ |title=Erling Haaland: Premier League Player Watch |website=The Coaches' Voice |date=25 February 2020 |access-date=26 May 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111907/https://www.coachesvoice.com/cv/erling-haaland-manchester-city-borussia-dortmund/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SOP2>{{cite web |url=https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/player-analysis-erling-haaland/ |title=Player Analysis: Erling Haaland |date=12 April 2021 |access-date=26 May 2022 |archive-date=4 February 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230204201637/https://breakingthelines.com/player-analysis/player-analysis-erling-haaland/ |url-status=live}}</ref>

Haaland uses his body well when playing with his back to goal, protecting the ball effectively as he tries to bring it under control. He uses his strength to secure possession when under pressure and is also effective in providing his team's defenders with some respite following a clearance. His creativity is most apparent when he drifts into the left inside channel. His primary aim is always to get a shot off, but he also has the vision and skill to pick out a delayed run from midfield in the centre. His ability to carry the ball at pace also helps create for others, especially on the counter-attack.<ref name=SOP3>{{cite web |url=https://themastermindsite.com/2021/03/09/erling-haaland-player-analysis/ |title=Erling Haaland – Player Analysis |date=9 March 2021 |access-date=26 May 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111815/https://themastermindsite.com/2021/03/09/erling-haaland-player-analysis/ |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name=SOP4>{{cite web |url=https://onenil.medium.com/erling-braut-h%C3%A5land-a-complete-analytical-breakdown-of-why-he-is-so-special-c068ae0b7539 |title=Erling Braut Håland: A complete analytical breakdown of why he is so special |date=29 October 2020 |access-date=26 May 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111812/https://onenil.medium.com/erling-braut-h%C3%A5land-a-complete-analytical-breakdown-of-why-he-is-so-special-c068ae0b7539 |url-status=live}}</ref> Even though he is less involved in possession than a typical striker, his calmness, patience, timing, and off-the-ball movement have a huge impact in build-up plays.<ref>{{cite web |title=Erling Haaland: Why FWA Footballer of the Year award must go to Manchester City's unique scoring phenomenon |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12877150/erling-haaland-why-fwa-footballer-of-the-year-award-must-go-to-manchester-citys-unique-scoring-phenomenon |date=11 May 2023 |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230511203158/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11095/12877150/erling-haaland-why-fwa-footballer-of-the-year-award-must-go-to-manchester-citys-unique-scoring-phenomenon |archive-date=11 May 2023 |work=Sky Sports |last=Bate |first=Adam}}</ref>

Haaland idolises [[Zlatan Ibrahimović]] and [[Cristiano Ronaldo]], but also cites [[Michu]], [[Jamie Vardy]], [[Sergio Agüero]] and [[Robin van Persie]] as inspirations, and credits [[Virgil van Dijk]] and [[Sergio Ramos]] as two of the toughest defenders he has played against.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/uefa-champions-league/story/3955668/meet-erling-haalandthe-teenage-striker-who-idolizes-zlataneats-like-ronaldo-and-scores-goals-like-them-both?platform=amp |title=Meet Erling Haaland, the teenage striker who idolizes Zlatan, eats like Ronaldo and scores goals like them both |work=ESPN |date=1 October 2019|access-date=1 September 2022|archive-date=17 April 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111816/https://www.espn.com/soccer/uefa-champions-league/story/3955668/meet-erling-haalandthe-teenage-striker-who-idolizes-zlataneats-like-ronaldo-and-scores-goals-like-them-both?platform=amp|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/51633521 |title=Erling Braut Haaland has an unusual footballing hero in ex-Swansea star Michu |publisher=BBC Sport |date=25 February 2020 |access-date=19 April 2022 |archive-date=17 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230417111816/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/51633521 |url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |title=Erling Haaland: Borussia Dortmund striker on Jamie Vardy inspiration, Flow Kingz reunion and more |date=27 January 2022 |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/12526621/erling-haaland-borussia-dortmund-striker-on-jamie-vardy-inspiration-flow-kingz-reunion-and-more |website=Sky Sports |archive-url=https://archive.today/20220127182744/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/12526621/erling-haaland-borussia-dortmund-striker-on-jamie-vardy-inspiration-flow-kingz-reunion-and-more |archive-date=27 January 2022}}</ref>

After scoring a goal, Haaland is known to perform a "meditation" celebration, in which he assumes the [[lotus position]];<ref name=":2">{{Cite web |date=10 June 2023 |title=Explaining what Erling Haaland's goal celebrations mean — from yoga meditation pose to mid-air leaps &#124; Sporting News |url=https://www.sportingnews.com/us/soccer/news/erling-haaland-goal-celebrations-mean-yoga-meditation-pose/ulzhwxy88pffepo0znhvbcsf |access-date=2 March 2025 |website=www.sportingnews.com |language=en-us}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=11 March 2020 |title=Haaland Responds to PSG Mocking His Meditation Celebration |url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/haaland-responds-to-psg-mocking-his-meditation-celebration-29824740 |access-date=2 March 2025 |website=OneFootball |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=27 July 2024 |title='I feel super powerful': How meditation helps soccer players get in the zone |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/40596685/mediation-soccer-stars-erling-haaland-sarah-gorden-griffin-dorsey |access-date=2 March 2025 |work=ESPN |language=en}}</ref> the celebration has been featured in the [[FIFA (video game series)|FIFA]] series of video games.<ref name=":2" />

=== Reception ===
After his record breaking first season in England, [[Gary Neville]] proclaimed that Haaland is "truly unique" and that he has the skill and strength of [[Wayne Rooney]] and the talent and finishing of Harry Kane and [[Ronaldo (Brazilian footballer)|Ronaldo]].<ref>{{cite web |last=Neville |first=Gary |date=3 May 2023 |title=Gary Neville: Unique Erling Haaland is Harry Kane, Wayne Rooney and Ronaldo combined |url=https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29326/12870656/gary-neville-unique-erling-haaland-is-harry-kane-wayne-rooney-and-cristiano-ronaldo-combined |archive-url=https://archive.today/20230503123246/https://www.skysports.com/football/news/29326/12870656/gary-neville-unique-erling-haaland-is-harry-kane-wayne-rooney-and-cristiano-ronaldo-combined |archive-date=3 May 2023 |work=Sky Sports |location=United Kingdom}}</ref> His manager at City, [[Pep Guardiola]], opined that Haaland has the potential to get even better.<ref>{{Cite web |date=2 May 2023 |title=Haaland has desire to get even better – Guardiola |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/65464392 |access-date=15 January 2024 |publisher=BBC Sport |language=en-GB}}</ref> In 2022, [[Jürgen Klopp]] labelled Haaland as the "best striker in the world" and stated that "physically he sets new standards, the combination of being really physical and technical and sensational awareness, his orientation on the pitch is exceptional,<ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-04-14 |title=Barcelona's Lamine Yamal breaks Erling Haaland Champions League record with Atletico Madrid strike |url=https://www.sportsmole.co.uk/football/barcelona/champions-league/news/erling-eclipsed-as-yamal-breaks-two-champions-league-records-with-barca-strike_595699.html |access-date=2026-04-17 |website=Sports Mole |language=en-GB}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |date=2026-04-17 |title='It's like a final!' - Erling Haaland sends defiant title warning to Arsenal ahead of massive Man City showdown {{!}} Goal.com India |url=https://www.goal.com/en-in/lists/erling-haaland-man-city-arsenal-premier-league-title-race-warning/blt48dc6061dd13a7ba |access-date=2026-04-17 |website=www.goal.com |language=en-IN}}</ref> he knows always where the decisive gaps are, barely offside".<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 October 2022 |title=ERLING HAALAND IS THE 'BEST STRIKER IN THE WORLD', SAYS JURGEN KLOPP AHEAD OF MANCHESTER CITY SHOWDOWN |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/premier-league/2022-2023/erling-haaland-is-the-best-striker-in-the-world-says-jurgen-klopp-ahead-of-manchester-city-showdown_sto9185901/story.shtml |access-date=15 January 2024 |website=eurosport.com}}</ref> In 2024, [[FIFPRO]] declared him to be "the deadliest striker in football today".<ref>{{Cite web |date=13 January 2024 |title=Erling Haaland: A record marksman |url=https://www.fifpro.org/en/supporting-players/player-influence/world11/erling-haaland-a-record-marksman |access-date=15 January 2024 |website=fifpro.org}}</ref> For his achievements, he has also been hailed as the greatest Norwegian player of all time.<ref name="e022">{{cite web | last=Begley | first=Emlyn | title=Erling Haaland: How Man City striker fired Norway to 2026 World Cup | website=BBC Sport | date=16 November 2025 | url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/articles/cpv18vznj78o | access-date=3 December 2025}}</ref><ref name="u256">{{cite web | last=Smith | first=Rory | title=Haaland, Odegaard and Norway's desperate quest to end decades in the wilderness | website=The Athletic | date=22 March 2025 | url=https://www.nytimes.com/athletic/6221042/2025/03/22/norway-haaland-odegaard-2026-world-cup/ | access-date=3 December 2025}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Haaland is the son of the Norwegian former footballer [[Alf-Inge Haaland|Alfie Haaland]] and former women's [[heptathlon]] athlete Gry Marita Braut.<ref>{{cite web |title=Molde starlet Erling Braut Haland wants to follow father Alf-Inge and play for Leeds United. |publisher=Talksport |date=10 February 2017 |access-date=3 January 2018 |url=https://talksport.com/football/molde-starlet-erling-braut-haland-wants-follow-father-alf-inge-and-play-leeds-united |archive-date=4 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180104015405/https://talksport.com/football/molde-starlet-erling-braut-haland-wants-follow-father-alf-inge-and-play-leeds-united |url-status=live}}</ref> In a 2017 interview with Norwegian newspaper ''[[Aftenposten]]'', Haaland said that "The dream is to win the Premier League with Leeds".<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.aftenposten.no/article/ap-GGP7A6.html |title=Vraket utlandet for å spille under Solskjær |newspaper=Aftenposten |language=no |access-date=17 September 2019 |archive-date=25 August 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200825175301/https://www.aftenposten.no/article/ap-GGP7A6.html |url-status=live}}</ref> From his mother's side, he is a member of the {{ill|Braut (slekt)|no|lt=Braut}} footballing family, and his first cousins [[Jonatan Braut Brunes]], {{ill|Emma Braut Brunes|no}}, and {{ill|Albert Braut Tjåland|no}} are also professional footballers,<ref>{{Cite web |last=Fotballforbund |first=Norges |title=Jonatan Braut Brunes – Profil |url=https://www.fotball.no/fotballdata/person/profil/?fiksId=3707103|access-date=20 August 2021 |website=fotball.no – Norges Fotballforbund |language=no|archive-date=6 March 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230306201804/https://www.fotball.no/fotballdata/person/profil/?fiksId=3707103|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |title=Haaland's cousin is making waves in Norway... with 64 goals in 37 matches! |newspaper=Marca|location=Spain |date=5 March 2021 |access-date=7 March 2021 |url=https://www.marca.com/en/football/transfer-market/2021/03/05/604265b722601dac158b4612.html |archive-date=7 March 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307061031/https://www.marca.com/en/football/transfer-market/2021/03/05/604265b722601dac158b4612.html |url-status=live}}</ref> as was his great-uncle [[Gabriel Høyland]].

Haaland is a practitioner of [[meditation]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4226109/why-dortmund-star-erling-haaland-could-become-the-worlds-best-footballer |last=Teng |first=Elaine |title=Why Dortmund star Erling Haaland could become the world's best footballer |work=ESPN |date=5 November 2020 |access-date=20 February 2021 |archive-date=19 February 2021|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210219192252/https://www.espn.com/soccer/borussia-dortmund/story/4226109/why-dortmund-star-erling-haaland-could-become-the-worlds-best-footballer|url-status=live}}</ref>

In 2016, Haaland and his [[Norway national under-17 football team|Norway under-17]] teammates [[Erik Botheim]] and [[Erik Tobias Sandberg]], under the group name Flow Kingz, released a single entitled "Kygo jo", which has over 14 million views on YouTube.<ref name="Easwar 2022">{{cite web |last=Easwar |first=Nisanth V. |title=Erling Haaland & Flow Kingz: Man City star's rap 'career' explained |website=Goal (website) |date=13 June 2022 |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/erling-haaland-and-flow-kingz-man-city-star-rap-career/blt9cec18a5e80401eb |access-date=26 April 2023 |archive-date=26 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426162650/https://www.goal.com/en/news/erling-haaland-and-flow-kingz-man-city-star-rap-career/blt9cec18a5e80401eb |url-status=live}}</ref><ref name="SPORTbible 2022">{{cite web |title=Erling Haaland's 'Flow Kingz' rap music video has been translated into English, the lyrics are hilarious |website=SPORTbible |date=8 October 2022 |url=https://www.sportbible.com/football/erling-haaland-manchester-city-flow-kingz-music-video-20221008 |access-date=26 April 2023 |archive-date=26 April 2023 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20230426162650/https://www.sportbible.com/football/erling-haaland-manchester-city-flow-kingz-music-video-20221008 |url-status=live}}</ref>

In October 2024, Haaland announced via social media that he was expecting a first child with girlfriend Isabel Haugseng Johansen.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://sports.yahoo.com/erling-haaland-drops-announcement-expecting-213300828.html |title=Erling Haaland drops announcement on expecting first child with girlfriend Isabel Haugseng Johansen |website=Yahoo Sports |date=10 October 2024 |access-date=10 October 2024}}</ref> His son was born in December.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Wiseman |first=Ciaran |date=5 October 2025 |title='Never felt better' – Erling Haaland reveals heartwarming reason behind his best ever run |url=https://talksport.com/football/3616570/erling-haaland-son-goal-man-city-premier-league/ |access-date=14 January 2026 |website=talkSPORT}}</ref>

In December 2025, Haaland and his father purchased the 1594 edition of [[Snorri Sturluson]]'s chronicles at an auction for 1.3 million [[Norwegian kroner]], setting a national record for a book sale in Norway. He later donated the volume, which details the history of medieval [[Norsemen|Norse]] kings, to his home municipality for display in a library, saying he wanted local residents to be able to read about historical figures from their area.<ref name="q005">{{citation | title=Haaland trades goals for sagas with record-breaking Viking book | url=https://www.reuters.com/lifestyle/haaland-trades-goals-sagas-with-record-breaking-viking-book-2026-03-25/ | language=en-US | access-date=26 March 2026 | page=}}</ref>

In February 2026, he was listed on ''[[The Sunday Times]]'' tax list with an estimated £16.9 million.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Watts |first=Robert |date=31 January 2026 |title=Who are the UK’s biggest taxpayers? The 2026 Tax List revealed |url=https://www.thetimes.com/money/tax/article/uk-100-biggest-taxpayers-2026-tax-list-nqsjk2bvn |access-date=3 March 2026 |website=The Sunday Times |language=en}}</ref>

Haaland is set to make his feature film voice acting debut, playing a Viking also named Haaland in the animated film ''ViQueens''. The movie is scheduled for release on Christmas of 2026. It is directed and co-written by [[Harald Zwart]], who also directed [[The Karate Kid (2010 film)|''The Karate Kid'']] (2010). Zwart said "Erling has already become a kind of real-life Viking icon around the world".<ref>{{cite news |title=Erling Haaland to make film acting debut – as a Viking called Haaland |url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2026/may/15/erling-haaland-film-acting-debut-viqueens-viking |work=The Guardian |date=15 May 2026 |access-date=26 May 2026 |archive-date=15 May 2026 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20260515170159/https://www.theguardian.com/film/2026/may/15/erling-haaland-film-acting-debut-viqueens-viking| url-status=live}}{{cbignore}}</ref>

